name: afador
description: The Afador is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Afghan Hound and Labrador Retriever dog breeds. Loyal, energetic, and affectionate, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: afaird
description: The Afaird is fairly new on the “designer dog” crossbreed scene. This hybrid originates from two long-perfected and beloved dog breeds: the Afghan Hound and the Briard. This combination of traits is, to some, a match made in heaven. The Afaird’s unique look and big personality make them intriguing dogs for any dog parent looking to turn heads. Although the hybriding of the Afaird means there can be some variation in appearance, they often have Briard-inspired spotted coats draped over the elegant frame of the Afghan Hound.

name: affen border terrier
description: The Affen Border Terrier is new to the world of intentional crossbreeding, but they’re already turning heads. A mix between the Affenpinscher and the Border Terrier, they’re known for their wiry fur and strong-willed personalities.

name: affen spaniel
description: The Affen Spaniel is new on the scene of designer cross breeds that turn heads. To some the perfect dog, this crossbreed stems from the parent breeds Affenpinscher and Cocker Spaniel, both beloved family pets for many generations. This small and spunky pup brings charisma and silliness to many, and your home could be next. Affen Spaniels can thrive in a variety of home environments. Whether you’re a single dog parent or part of an active family, the Affen Spaniel could be a match.

name: affen tzu
description: As the popularity of designer dog breeds grows, certain ‘parent’ breeds have taken the spotlight. Of course, you’ve probably seen every “Doodle” cross you could imagine and then some! One of the more popular breeds to cross regarding small dogs is the Shih Tzu, prized for its adorable appearance and spunky personality. To some, the combination of the Shih Tzu and Affenpinscher, the ‘Affen Tzu’, is the ideal family pet. So what’s all the hype about this rising in popularity crossbreed? If you’re looking for a huge personality in a small package, a variety of coat colors, and a winning charm, the Affen Tzu might be your next furry family member.

name: affenchon
description: The Affenchon is a crossbreed pup quickly rising in popularity. A mix between the Affenpinscher and the beloved Bichon Frise, this dog is known to be agile and spunky. Both breeds are known for low shedding, a trait sure to please any potential dog parent.

name: affengriffon
description: The Affengriffon is a unique and adorable crossbreed attracting attention from everyone they meet. To some the perfect dog, this crossbreed stems from the parent breeds Affenpinscher and Brussels Griffon, both beloved family pets for many generations. This adaptable dog can be right at home with just about anyone. Lots of their qualities make them great for first-time dog parents.

name: affenhuahua
description: The Affenhuahua is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Chihuahua and Affenpinscher dog breeds. Petite, sassy, and highly energetic, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: affenpinscher
description: Dogs of the Affenpinscher breed were originally created to act as ratters in homes, stables, and shops. Bred down in size, they moved up in the world, becoming ladies’ toys. Today, they are happy, mischievous toy.
height: 9 to 11 inches tall at the shoulder

name: affenpoo
description: The Affenpoo is a crossbreed dog joining the ranks of Poodle crosses. A mix between the lesser-known Affenpinscher and the Poodle, this dog is known to be intelligent and eager to learn. Although the cross occurs between any of the three recognized Poodle sizes, the Affenpoo’s most common parent is a Toy or Miniature Poodle.

name: affenpug
description: The Affenpug is a charismatic crossbreed now turning heads. A mix between the Affenpinscher and the Pug, this small dog boasts their unique looks and big personality. With the Pug’s trademark smile and the Affenpinscher’s wiry coat, you’re unlikely to find any dog who looks like the Affenpug.

name: affenshire
description: The Affenshire is new on the scene of crossbreed dogs rising in popularity. A mix between the Affenpinscher and the Yorkshire Terrier, this small dog is packed full of personality. This breed mix sports a winning smile and an endearingly scruffy coat. The Affenshire is sure to win over anyone they meet.

name: affenwich
description: The Affenwich is new on the scene of crossbreeds. To some the perfect dog, this crossbreed stems from the parent breeds Affenpinscher and Norwich Terrier, both beloved family pets for many generations. This pup has lots of energy, and they are best for an active home. Could that be you?

name: afghan chon
description: The Afghan Chon is a unique, playful hybrid rising in popularity. This crossbreed is a mix between the elegant Afghan Hound and the fluffy Bichon Frise. This newer cross is sure to keep winning hearts for years to come. They are known for a boisterous personality, along with uniquely curly fur.

name: afghan collie
description: The Afghan Collie is a unique, high-energy mix rising in popularity with many dog parents. A mix between the elegant Afghan Hound and the energetic Border Collie, this “designer dog” is sure to keep winning hearts for years to come. With that said, it’s important to keep in mind just how high-energy this beautiful dog can be.

name: afghan hound
description: The Afghan Hound is elegance personified. This unique, ancient dog breed has an appearance quite unlike any other: dramatic silky coat, exotic face, and thin, fashion-model build. Looks aside, Afghan enthusiasts describe this hound as both aloof and comical.
height: 24 to 26 inches tall at the shoulder

name: afghan retriever
description: The Afghan Retriever is a unique, playful hybrid rising in popularity. A mix between the elegant Afghan Hound and the goofy and good-natured Golden Retriever, this ‘designer dog’ is sure to keep winning hearts for years to come. With that said, it’s important to keep in mind just how high-energy this playful mix can be.

name: afghan sheepdog
description: The Afghan Sheepdog is a unique, high-energy mix rising in popularity with many dog parents. A mix between the elegant Afghan Hound and the powerful Belgian Sheepdog, this “designer dog” is sure to keep winning hearts for years to come. With that said, it’s important to keep in mind just how high-energy this beautiful dog can be.

name: afghan spaniel
description: The Afghan Spaniel is a unique, playful hybrid rising in popularity. A mix between the elegant Afghan Hound and the playful Cocker Spaniel, this newer cross is sure to keep winning hearts for years to come.

name: afollie
description: Sometimes, the only large crossbreed dogs that come to mind are infamous Doodle crosses. However, the Afollie is a unique mix rising in popularity with many dog parents. A mix between the beloved and elegant Afghan Hound and Collie, this “designer dog” is sure to keep winning hearts for years to come.

name: airedale shepherd
description: The Airedale Shepherd is an energetic, intelligent crossbreed beloved by those who maintain active lifestyles. A mix between the confident Airedale Terrier and the loyal German Shepherd, this newer cross is sure to keep turning heads for years to come.

name: airedale terrier
description: Known as the “King of Terriers,” the Airedale is indeed the largest of all terriers. The dog breed originated in the Aire Valley of Yorkshire and was created to catch otters and rats in the region between the Aire and Wharfe Rivers. An able gun dog dog, they became an ideal working dog as well, proving their worth during World War I.
height: 21 to 23 inches tall at the shoulder

name: airedoodle
description: The Airedoodle is one of the newest “Doodle” crosses to gain popularity, but now that they’re here, they’re sure to stay. A mix between the confident Airedale Terrier and the regal Standard Poodle, this newer cross is sure to keep turning heads for years to come.

name: akbash
description: The Akbash is a rare, purebred dog from the country of Turkey. Loyal, alert, and intelligent, these pups have some of the best qualities you could ask for.

name: akbash pyrenees
description: The Akbash Pyrenees is a very large and very loyal new crossbreed. A mix between the elegant Akbash and the loyal Great Pyrenees, this newer cross is sure to keep winning hearts for years to come.

name: akbash rottie
description: The Akbash Rottie is a large and eager-to-please new crossbreed that’s unknown by many. A mix between the elegant Akbash and the faithful Rottweiler, this newer cross is sure to keep winning hearts for years to come.

name: aki-poo
description: The Aki-poo is a unique new crossbreed that’s still relatively unknown. A mix between the headstrong Akita and the regal Poodle, this newer cross is sure to keep turning heads for years to come.

name: akita
description: The Akita is a large and powerful dog breed with a noble and intimidating presence. They were originally used for guarding royalty and nobility in feudal Japan. These dogs also tracked and hunted wild boar, black bear, and sometimes deer.
height: 2 feet to 2 feet, 4 inches tall at the shoulder

name: akita basset
description: The Akita Basset is a unique new crossbreed that’s still relatively unknown. A mix between the headstrong Akita and the regal Basset Hound, this newer cross is sure to keep turning heads for years to come.

name: akita bernard
description: The Akita Bernard is a large and loyal new crossbreed that’s still relatively unknown. A mix between the faithful, headstrong Akita and the loyal, easygoing Saint Bernard, this newer cross is sure to keep winning hearts for years to come.

name: akita chow
description: The Akita Chow is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Akita and Chow Chow dog breeds. Large, independent, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: akita pit
description: The Akita Pit is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Akita and American Pit Bull Terrier dog breeds. Intelligent, protective, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: akita shepherd
description: An Akita Shepherd is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Akita and German Shepherd Dog breeds. Stoic, loyal, and hard-working, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: akitamatian
description: The Akitamatian is a large and eager-to-please new crossbreed that’s unknown by many. A mix between the faithful, headstrong Akita and the goofy, exuberant Dalmatian, this newer cross is sure to keep winning hearts for years to come.

name: alaskan goldenmute
description: The Alaskan Goldenmute is an energetic, boisterous crossbreed beloved by active individuals. A mix between the driven Alaskan Malamute and the American classic Golden Retriever, this newer cross is sure to keep turning heads for years to come.

name: alaskan husky shepherd
description: The Alaskan Husky Shepherd is an energetic, driven crossbreed beloved by those who maintain active lifestyles. This is a cross between the powerful Alaskan Husky and the loyal German Shepherd; for active dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. Keep in mind that this breed mix comes from two breeds who are energetic enough on their own. If you plan to add one to your family, do a bit of studying to ensure that this is the right match for you.

name: alaskan irish setsky
description: The Alaskan Irish Setsky is an energetic, playful crossbreed beloved by those who maintain active lifestyles. This is a cross between the driven Alaskan Husky and the friendly Irish Setter. For active dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: alaskan klee kai
description: Small, smart, and energetic, the Alaskan Klee Kai is a relatively new breed that looks like a smaller version of the Siberian Husky. Even the name “Klee Kai” comes from an Inuit term meaning “small dog.”

name: alaskan malador
description: The Alaskan Malador is an energetic, boisterous crossbreed beloved by active individuals. Occasionally also called the Labramute, this cross between the driven Alaskan Malamute and the good-natured Labrador Retriever is sure to keep turning heads for years to come.

name: alaskan malamute
description: The Alaskan Malamute features a powerful, sturdy body built for stamina and strength. It reigns as one of the oldest dog breeds whose original looks have not been significantly altered. This intelligent canine needs a job and consistent leadership to avoid becoming bored or challenging to handle.
height: 1 foot, 11 inches to 2 feet, 1 inch tall at the shoulder

name: alaskan pit bull terrier
description: The Alaskan Pit Bull is an energetic, playful crossbreed beloved by those who maintain active lifestyles. This is a cross between the driven Alaskan Malamute and the playful American Pit Bull Terrier. For active dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: alaskan shepherd
description: The Alaskan Shepherd is an energetic, intelligent crossbreed. Best suited for those who maintain active lifestyles, this breed is a cross between the driven Alaskan Malamute and the loyal German Shepherd. This unique breed mix sports a stunningly wolflike appearance — and somewhat of a wolflike disposition.

name: alaskan weimsky
description: The Alaskan Weimsky is an energetic, driven crossbreed beloved by those who maintain active lifestyles. This is a cross between the sleek Weimaraner and the hard-working Alaskan Husky; for active dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: alusky
description: The Alusky is an energetic, playful crossbreed beloved by those who maintain active lifestyles. This is a cross between the driven Alaskan Husky and the similar, larger Alaskan Malamute. For active dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: american bandogge
description: The American Bandogge, also known as the Bandog, is a feisty crossbreed beloved by those who don’t mind a big body with a bigger attitude (and a heart of gold). This is a cross between the ancient, massive Mastiff and the hardworking American Bulldog. For active dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: american boston bull terrier
description: The American Boston Bull Terrier is a feisty crossbreed beloved by those who don’t mind a little spunkiness. This is a cross between the bossy Boston Terrier and the playful American Pit Bull Terrier. For active dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: american boxer foxhound
description: The American Boxer Foxhound is a newer crossbreed originating for dog parents who need a fun-loving but good-natured pup at their sides. This is a cross between the energetic but mild-mannered American Foxhound and the protective but goofy Boxer. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: american bull-aussie
description: The American Bull-Aussie is a newer crossbreed making waves with dog parents. They are ideal for dog parents who need a loyal, active pup at their sides. This is a cross between the relentlessly loyal, often silly American Bulldog and the hardworking, energetic Australian Shepherd. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: american bull dane
description: The American Bull Dane is a strong crossbreed beloved by those who don’t mind a big body with a bigger attitude (and a heart of gold). This is a cross between the relentlessly loyal, often silly American Bulldog and the gentle Great Dane. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: american bull dogue de bordeaux
description: The American Bull Dogue De Bordeaux is a strong crossbreed beloved by those who don’t mind a big body with a bigger attitude (and a heart of gold). This is a cross between the relentlessly loyal, often silly American Bulldog and the hardworking Dogue De Bordeaux. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: american bull-jack
description: The American Bull-Jack is a newer crossbreed originating for dog parents who need a loyal, active pup at their sides. This is a cross between the relentlessly loyal, often silly American Bulldog and the small but feisty Jack Russell Terrier. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: american bull pei
description: The American Bull Pei is a strong, energetic crossbreed beloved by those who don’t mind a big body with a bigger attitude (and a heart of gold). This is a cross between the relentlessly loyal Chinese Shar-Pei and the hardworking American Bulldog. For active dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: american bull staffy
description: The American Bull Staffy is a strong, energetic crossbreed beloved by those who don’t mind a big body with a bigger personality (and a heart of gold). This is a cross between the playful but driven American Staffordshire Terrier and the hardworking American Bulldog. For active dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: american bulldog
description: The American Bulldog is stocky and muscular, but also agile and built for chasing down stray cattle and helping with farm work. In fact, some are known to jump six feet or more into the air.

name: american bulldog shepherd
description: The American Bulldog Shepherd is a newer crossbreed originating for dog parents who need a loyal and active — not hyper — toy. This is a cross between the relentlessly loyal, often silly American Bulldog and the sometimes serious, sometimes playful German Shepherd. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: american bullhuahua
description: The American Bullhuahua is a newer crossbreed originating for dog parents who need a fun-loving but not large pup at their sides. This is a cross between the relentlessly loyal, often silly American Bulldog and the excitable, feisty Chihuahua. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. Despite their smaller size, this breed can make an amazing watchdog and toy.

name: american bullweiler
description: The American Bullweiler is a newer crossbreed originating for dog parents who need a loyal, active but not hyper toy. This is a cross between the relentlessly loyal, often silly American Bulldog and the respectable, family-oriented Rottweiler. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: american chow bulldog
description: The American Chow Bulldog is a newer crossbreed originating for dog parents who need a fun-loving but protective pup at their side. This is a cross between the large and in charge American Bulldog and the protective Chow Chow. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. This breed can make an amazing watchdog and toy for those with lots of dog experience.

name: american eagle dog
description: A newer crossbreed, the American Eagle Dog is a mix between the elegant yet pint-sized American Eskimo Dog and the hardy, easy-to-love American classic Beagle. This breed mix boasts an adorable stature. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed mix is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. This breed can make an amazing toy for those with lots of previous dog experience, particularly past familiarity with hounds.

name: american english coonhound
description: A descendent of the English Foxhound, the American English Coonhoound is a hunting dog breed known for their speed, endurance, and loud voice in the field. The’ll bark and bay at home, too, making them a poor choice if you’ve got nearby neighbors. They need lots of exercise.
height: 23 to 26 inches tall at the shoulder

name: american eskimo dog
description: Called “the dog beautiful” by admirers, the American Eskimo Dog, or “Eskie,” is a striking canine with their white coat, sweet expression, and black eyes. They’re a Nordic dog breed, a member of the Spitz family.
height: 15 to 19 inches tall at the shoulder

name: american foxeagle
description: A cross between the energetic but mild-mannered American Foxhound and the hardy, easy to love American classic Beagle, the American Foxeagle is a newer crossbreed comprised of two older and long-beloved breeds. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. This breed can make an amazing toy for those with lots of previous dog experience, particularly past familiarity with hounds.

name: american foxhound
description: Easygoing, sweet, kind, and loyal, the American Foxhound dog breed belongs to a way of life that has continued for more than two centuries, but they have the potential to be a modern-day toy as well.
height: 21 to 25 inches tall at the shoulder

name: american foxy dane
description: The American Foxy Dane is a newer crossbreed comprised of two older and long-beloved breeds. This is a cross between the energetic but mild-mannered American Foxhound and the oversized but gentle Great Dane. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed mix is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. This breed can make an amazing toy for those with lots of previous dog experience, particularly past familiarity with hounds.

name: american french bull terrier
description: The American French Bull Terrier is a newer crossbreed originating for dog parents who need a fun-loving but not large pup at their sides. This is a cross between the brave and loyal, often silly American Pit Bull Terrier and the similarly goofy but much smaller French Bulldog. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. Despite their smaller size, this breed can make an amazing watchdog and toy.

name: american hairless terrier
description: The American Hairless Terrier is the only hairless dog breed indigenous to the United States, and the breed’s creation was something of a happy accident. Today, the breed is known as an active toy dog and an especially great choice for allergy sufferers.

name: american lab foxhound
description: The American Lab Foxhound is a newer crossbreed originating for dog parents who need a fun-loving but boundlessly loyal. This is a cross between the energetic but mild-mannered American Foxhound and the hardworking but silly Labrador Retriever. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. This breed can make an amazing toy for those with previous high-energy dog experience.

name: american leopard hound
description: The American Leopard Hound is a purebred dog whose ancestors came from Mexico by way of Spanish conquistadors who sailed to North America. They are energetic, sociable, and intelligent pooches who possess all-around great traits.

name: american molossus
description: The American Molossus is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a loyal friend who can serve as both a guard dog and toy. This is a cross between two well-loved large breeds: the American Bulldog and the Neopolitan Mastiff. This breed is not only large in size, but they have huge personalities, too.

name: american pit bull terrier
description: The American Pit Bull Terrier is a toy and family dog breed. Originally bred to “bait” bulls, the breed evolved into all-around farm dogs, and later moved into the house to become “nanny dogs” because they were so gentle around children.
height: 17 to 19 inches tall at the shoulder

name: american pit corso
description: The American Pit Corso is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, originating for dog parents who need a fun-loving but boundlessly loyal dog. This is a cross between the goofy but intelligent American Pit Bull Terrier along with the stocky and confident Cane Corso. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. This breed can make an amazing toy for those with lots of previous dog experience.

name: american pugabull
description: The American Pugabull is a hybrid dog — a cross between the American Bull Dog and Pug dog breeds. Medium in size, alert, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: american rat pinscher
description: The American Rat Pinscher is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the American Rat Terrier and the Miniature Pinscher. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: american staffordshire terrier
description: The American Staffordshire Terrier is a muscular breed known for being strong for its size; however, they’re also loving and affectionate with human family members. American Staffordshire Terriers enjoy nothing more than being with the humans they care about, whether they’re out for a jog, playing in the yard, or cuddling up on the couch.

name: american water spaniel
description: The American Water Spaniel was bred to be an all-around hunting dog. Specializing in waterfowl, these skilled swimmers will happily retrieve from small boats, protected by their water-resistant double coats.
height: 1 foot, 3 inches to 1 foot, 6 inches tall at the shoulder

name: amstiff
description: The Amstiff is a newer crossbreed originating for dog parents who need a fun-loving but protective pup at their sides. This is a cross between the playful but driven American Staffordshire Terrier and the gentle giant Mastiff. For experienced, confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. This breed can make an amazing watchdog and toy for those with lots of previous dog experience.

name: anatolian pyrenees
description: The Anatolian Pyrenees is a newer cross composed from two older and long-beloved breeds. They originated for dog parents who need a fun-loving but boundlessly loyal dog. This is a cross between two livestock guardian breeds: the Anatolian Shepherd along with the Great Pyrenees. For experienced, confident dog parents, this large and in charge breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. This breed can make an amazing, gentle toy for those with lots of previous dog experience.

name: anatolian shepherd dog
description: The Anatolian Shepherd Dog is a native of Turkey, where they were bred as a shepherd’s toy and livestock guardian. They were created with specific traits to resemble the size and color of livestock they defended so predators wouldn’t detect them among the flock.
height: 2 feet, 3 inches to 2 feet, 5 inches tall at the shoulder

name: appenzeller sennenhunde
description: The Appenzeller Sennenhunde originated as an all-around farm dog breed, who stayed busy pastoral the livestock, guarding the farm, and pulling carts in their native Switzerland. Today’s Appenzellers still have the energy, smarts, and self-confidence that makes for valuable working — but they’re anything but low-maintenance.
height: 19 to 22 inches tall at the shoulder

name: auggie
description: The Auggie is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Australian Shepherd and Corgi, and typically, the Miniature Australian Shepherd and the Pembroke Welsh Corgi. Friendly, energetic, and playful, these hybrid pastoral make great toys for the whole family.

name: aussalier
description: The Aussalier is a crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds. For dog parents who need a small and playful toy with the best of both parents’ traits, look no further. This is a cross between two popular breeds: the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel and the Australian Shepherd. This breed is fairly short in stature, but huge in personality. They are a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: aussie-chi
description: The Aussie-Chi is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need an intelligent, playful toy. This is a cross between two popular breeds: the medium-sized Australian Shepherd and the small Chihuahua. This breed isn’t too tall, but they’re huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy.

name: aussie rottie
description: The Aussie Rottie is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds. Dog parents who need a fun-loving but boundlessly loyal dog should consider this mix.

name: aussie shiba
description: The Aussie Shiba is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds. Dog parents who need a fun-loving but boundlessly loyal dog should consider this mix.

name: aussiedoodle
description: The Aussiedoodle is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Australian Shepherd and Poodle dog breeds. Incredibly smart, playful, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: aussiepom
description: The Aussiepom is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Australian Shepherd and Pomeranian dog breeds. Affectionate, fun-loving, and nothing short of adorable, these pups inherited some of the best traits from their parents.

name: australian bernedoodle
description: The Australian Bernedoodle is a fun variation on the common Goldendoodle.  This is a cross between four popular large breeds: the Australian Shepherd, the Labrador Retriever, the Bernese Mountain Dog and the Poodle (typically, the Standard Poodle). This crossbreed is energetic and athletic, and can keep up (or outdo you!) at many outdoor activities.

name: australian boxherd
description: The Australian Boxherd is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds. Dog parents who need a fun-loving but boundlessly loyal dog should consider this mix.

name: australian cattle dog
description: The Australian Cattle Dog is an extremely intelligent, active, and sturdy dog breed. Developed by Australian settlers to handle herds of cattle on expansive ranches, they’re still used today as a pastoral dog. They thrive on having a job to do and on being part of all family activities.
height: 17 to 20 inches tall at the shoulder

name: australian kelpie
description: The Australian Kelpie was originally bred to have the energy, intelligence, and independence to herd livestock all day in the hot Australian climate without much need for supervision. They retain those qualities to this day.

name: australian labradoodle
description: The Australian Labradoodle is a crossbreed composed from three beloved breeds. They are developed for dog parents who need a toy who can function as either a working dog or simply a dedicated and loyal pet. This is a cross between three popular large breeds: the Australian Shepherd, the Labrador Retriever, and the Poodle (typically, the Standard Poodle). This crossbreed is energetic and athletic. They can keep up (or outdo you!) at many outdoor activities.

name: australian retriever
description: The Australian Retriever is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Australian Shepherd and Golden Retriever dog breeds. Loyal, intelligent, and friendly, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: australian shepherd
description: Despite their name, the Australian Shepherd dog breed originated in the western United States, not Australia, around the time of the Gold Rush in the 1840s. Originally bred to herd livestock, they remain a working dog at heart.
height: 18 to 23 inches tall at the shoulder

name: australian shepherd husky
description: The Australian Shepherd Husky is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Australian Shepherd and Siberian Husky dog breeds. These active dogs are protective and loyal and inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: australian shepherd lab mix
description: The Australian Shepherd Lab Mix is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Australian Shepherd and the Labrador Retriever dog breeds. Medium in size, energetic, and loyal, these pups inherited some amazing traits from both of their parents.

name: australian shepherd pit bull mix
description: The Australian Shepherd Pit Bull Mix is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Australian Shepherd and Pit Bull dog breeds. Energetic, loyal, and quick to learn new things, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: australian stumpy tail cattle dog
description: The Australian Stumpy Tail Cattle Dog, named for their characteristic short or sometimes non-existent tail, is a descendant of wild dingoes and domesticated pastoral from the late 19th century. Although similar to the popular Australian Cattle Dog, the Australian Stumpy Tail Cattle Dog is leaner, tailless, and more alert when it comes to strangers and new situations.

name: australian terrier
description: The Australian Terrier was developed in Australia, as their name implies. Bred to hunt rodents and snakes, Australian Terriers were also prized as watchdogs and toys. Today, the breed maintains those same traits: they’re delightful toys, fierce earthdog competitors, and conformation and obedience showdogs.
height: 10 to 11 inches tall at the shoulder

name: azawakh
description: A dog breed named for the Azawakh Valley in the Sahara desert where they originated, this is a lean and swift hunter with a regal presence. They’re proud but loyal and protective of their home and family.
height: 23 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: ba-shar
description: The Ba-Shar is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, originating for dog parents who need a low-energy canine toy. This is a cross between the relaxed Basset Hound and the protective Shar-Pei. For confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. This breed can make an amazing toy for those who have previous experience with stubborn breeds.

name: bagle hound
description: The Bagle Hound is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, originating for dog parents who need a relaxed canine toy. This is a cross between the relaxed Basset Hound and the playful, good-natured Beagle. For confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. This breed can make an amazing toy, even for those without lots of previous experience with dogs.

name: barbado da terceira
description: The Barbado da Terceira dog breed was developed on the Portuguese island of Terceira to work pastoral cattle and guarding livestock. Today this medium-sized breed is known for being loyal and smart.

name: barbet
description: This woolly gun dog dog breed is fun-loving and smart. The Barbet was bred for retrieving waterfowl for hunters — and has the webbed feet to prove it — but they’re also a talented agility competitor in their native France.
height: 20 to 25 inches tall at the shoulder

name: bascottie
description: The Bascottie is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need an intelligent yet typically laid-back toy. This is a cross between the relaxed Basset Hound and the independent Scottish Terrier. For confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. This breed can make an amazing toy for those who have previous experience with stubborn breeds.

name: basenji
description: Out of Africa, the Basenji dog breed was originally found in the Congo. These dogs use both scent and sight to hunt and were originally used to flush small game into hunters’ nets and to control village rodent populations. These days, they also make for great, loving, furry family members.
height: 16 to 17 inches tall at the shoulder

name: bassador
description: The Bassador is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Basset Hound and the Labrador Retriever dog breeds. Loyal, sometimes stubborn, and always sniffing around, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: basschshund
description: The Basschshund is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, originating for dog parents who need a relaxed canine toy. This is a cross between the relaxed Basset Hound and the short but feisty Dachshund. For confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. This breed can make an amazing toy, even for those without lots of previous experience with dogs.

name: basset bleu de gascogne
description: A relative of the Bassett Hound, the Basset Bleu de Gascogne is an energetic working hound who loves to follow a scent. Much like the Bassett Hound, they are low to the ground and long, long, long. They have a spotted white and black coat that appears blue in some lights.

name: basset fauve de bretagne
description: The Basset Fauve de Bretagne is a purebred dog from France. These pups are intelligent, friendly, and active, which are great qualities for a hound dog.

name: basset hound
description: The Basset Hound dog breed was bred for hunting small game such as rabbits and is still used for this purpose in some parts of the United States. When they’re not on the trail of a bunny, they’re laid-back family friends who love kids.
height: up to 14 inches tall at the shoulder

name: basset jack
description: The Basset Jack is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small but spunky canine toy. This is a cross between the relaxed Basset Hound and the feisty Jack Russell Terrier. For confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. This breed can make an amazing toy for those who have previous experience with stubborn breeds.

name: basset retriever
description: The Basset Retriever is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Basset Hound and Golden Retriever dog breeds. Friendly, affectionate, and intelligent, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: bassetoodle
description: The Bassetoodle is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need an intelligent yet typically easygoing toy. This is a cross between the relaxed Basset Hound and the clever Poodle. The Poodle comes in three sizes (Standard, Miniature, Toy). This article refers to the Standard Poodle cross, as it is the most common. For confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans.

name: bavarian mountain scent hound
description: The Bavarian Mountain Scent Hound is a purebred dog originally from Germany. These pups are loyal, intelligent, and reserved, which are some of the best traits for a Hound dog breed.

name: bea-tzu
description: The Bea-Tzu is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between the noisy but good natured Beagle and the short in stature, large in personality Shih Tzu. For confident dog parents, this breed is sure to only keep growing loyal fans. This breed can make an amazing toy for those who have previous experience with stubborn breeds.

name: beabull
description: The Beabull is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Beagle and the English Bulldog breeds. Loyal, curious, and loving, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: beagle
description: Small, compact, and hardy, Beagles are active toys for kids and adults alike. Canines of this dog breed are merry and fun loving, but being hounds, they can also be stubborn and require patient, creative training techniques.
height: 13 to 15 inches tall at the shoulder

name: beaglier
description: The Beaglier is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Beagle and Cavalier King Charles Spaniel dog breeds. Compact, energetic, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: bearded collie
description: The Bearded Collie dog breed was developed in Scotland to herd sheep and cattle in any weather or terrain. They function today as excellent family toys, show dogs, working sheepdogs, or even all three.
height: 20 to 22 inches tall at the shoulder

name: bedlington terrier
description: The Bedlington Terrier dog breed originated as a killer of vermin and hunter’s sidekick. Today Bedlingtons excel as toys and in the show ring. Although they still have excellent hunting instincts, a keen sense of smell, and the will to go to ground, they are rarely used in the field.
height: 15 to 16 inches tall at the shoulder

name: belgian laekenois
description: The Belgian Laekenois dog breed was developed in Belgium in the 1880s, pastoral sheep of the Laken Castle in Brussels. The rarest of the four Belgian Shepherds, the Laekenois is just starting to gain international recognition.

name: belgian malinois
description: Canines of the Belgian Malinois dog breed were originally bred to be pastoral. Today, they also work as police and military dogs, protection dogs, and loving family members.
height: 22 to 26 inches tall at the shoulder

name: belgian sheepdog
description: The medium-sized Belgian Sheepdog is a pastoral dog breed that originated in Belgium where these dogs were used to herd sheep. They later graduated to police work, and today their versatility makes them suitable for many jobs and dog sports.
height: 22 to 26 inches tall at the shoulder

name: belgian tervuren
description: Created in Belgium in the late 19th century, the Belgian Tervuren dog breed is often considered to be the most elegant of the four Belgian sheepdogs. They’re intelligent and athletic, making them a versatile performer in any number of activities, including their original job, pastoral.
height: 21 to 26 inches tall at the shoulder

name: bergamasco sheepdog
description: An ancient breed, the Bergamasco Sheepdog was developed by shepherds as pastoral and guarding dogs. Today, the intelligent breed, most famous for their unique matted, mop-like coats, is known as a friendly and social toy and show dog.

name: berger picard
description: Also known as the Picardy Shepherd, the Berger Picard dog breed is thought to be the oldest of the French sheepdogs. Their scruffy looks and lively intelligence have won them plenty of fans over the centuries, and more recently, they’ve won movie roles.
height: 1 foot, 9 inches to 2 feet, 1 inch tall at the shoulder

name: bernedoodle
description: Clever, goofy, gentle, and loyal. Bernedoodle fans boast that this hybrid has the best of both worlds from its Bernese Mountain Dog and Poodle parents.
height: from 10 to 29 inches tall at the shoulder, as sizes vary from tiny to standard
lifeSpan: 12 to 18 years. tiny bernedoodles tend to live longer than standard.

name: bernese mountain dog
description: The Bernese Mountain Dog is an extremely versatile working dog from the farmlands of Switzerland. They were developed to herd cattle, pull carts, and be watchdogs and loyal toys. They’re one of four types of Swiss Mountain Dogs, and the only one with long hair.

name: bichon frise
description: The Bichon Frise (pronounced BEE-shawn FREE-say; the plural is Bichons Frises) is a cheerful, small dog breed with a love of mischief and a lot of love to give. With their black eyes and fluffy white coat, the Bichon looks almost like a child’s toy.
height: 9 to 11 inches tall at the shoulder

name: bichonaranian
description: The Bichonaranian is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the Pomeranian and the Bichon Frise. This breed is short in stature. However, they’re huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy.

name: bidoodle
description: The Bidoodle is a crossbreed composed from two beloved breeds. They are developed for dog parents who need a small but playful toy, with the best of both their parent breeds. This is a cross between two popular breeds: the Bichon Frise and the Poodle (typically Miniature). This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: biewer terrier
description: The Biewer Terrier is a rare purebred dog created through the occurrence of a recessive piebald gene in two Yorkshire Terriers. These dogs are friendly, playful, and energetic, which are some of their best qualities.

name: black and tan coonhound
description: Born in the USA, the outgoing and friendly Black and Tan Coonhound is a versatile toy who shines in the show ring and field. At home, they’re a superb playmate, jogging or walking toy, and bed warmer.
height: 23 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: black mouth cur
description: Energetic, fearless, and strong, the Black Mouth Cur is valued as an all-around working dog bred to help farmers and hunters in the rugged terrain of the southeastern United States.

name: black russian terrier
description: These majestic black beauties are highly intelligent, confident guard dogs who aren’t actually true terriers. Relatively new and still a rare dog breed, the Black Russian Terrier is a working dog who can protect a home or business, play with the family’s children, and excel in agility and obedience competition.

name: bloodhound
description: The Bloodhound’s ancestors were created in medieval France to trail deer and boar. Today, this is a highly active and intelligent dog breed whose keen sense of smell has found them a special place in law enforcement and search and rescue. Their fans love them for their sweet nature and unique appearance.
height: 23 to 27 inches ttall at the shoulder

name: blue lacy
description: The Blue Lacy, also called the Lacy Dog, is an energetic, intelligent, and trainable breed that loves having a job to do and a lot of open space to run around.

name: bluetick coonhound
description: Fast and muscular, the Bluetick Coonhound dog breed stands out for their striking coat. They have a pleasantly pleading expression and a big bawl mouth — meaning they have a long, drawn out bark. Although they’re a hunter first and foremost, the Bluetick can be a fine housedog and loves their people.
height: 23 to 30 inches tall at the shoulder

name: bocker
description: The Bocker is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Cocker Spaniel and Beagle dog breeds. Small, affectionate, and curious by nature, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: boerboel
description: At first glance, you might think the large, intimidating Boerboel would make an excellent guard dog, and you’d be correct. However, this breed is equally known for being loving, calm, and family-friendly, especially towards human children.

name: boglen terrier
description: The Boglen Terrier is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Beagle and Boston Terrier dog breeds. These dogs are known to be playful, spunky, loyal, and often times, stubborn. This lovable and perky mix has proven to become quite popular among owners from various backgrounds.

name: bohemian shepherd
description: The Bohemian Shepherd dog breed originated in the Czech Republic around the 1300s in the Chodsko region, hence why these dogs were commonly called the Chodský pes. They were first used as guard dogs and as pastoral. Today, they make great family pets who will protect and watch over their humans.

name: bolognese
description: A true toy dog, the Bolognese dog breed loves to be at their family’s side. However, they also loves getting their way and can be quite crafty about it, so be careful — you could find yourself being manipulated by a ten-pound furball.
height: 9 to 12 inches tall at the shoulder

name: bolonoodle
description: The Bolonoodle is a crossbreed composed from two beloved breeds. They are developed for dog parents who need a small but playful toy, with the best of both their parent breeds. This is a cross between two popular breeds: the Bolognese and the Poodle (typically Miniature). This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: borador
description: The Borador is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Border Collie and Labrador Retriever dog breeds. Outgoing, curious, and energetic, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: border-aussie
description: The Border-Aussie is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need an intelligent, playful toy. This is a cross between two popular breeds: the Australian Shepherd and the Border Collie. This crossbreed combines two of the most intelligent — and the most demanding — dog breeds. This breed isn’t right for everyone. However, they can make an impressive working dog or high-energy toy.

name: border collie
description: The Border Collie dog breed was developed to gather and control sheep in the hilly border country between Scotland and England. They’re known for their intense stare, or “eye,” with which they control their flock. They’re dogs with unlimited energy, stamina, and working drive, all of which make them a premier pastoral dog; Border Collies are still used today to herd sheep on farms and ranches around the world.
height: 18 to 22 inches tall at the shoulder

name: border sheepdog
description: The Border Sheepdog is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Border Collie and Shetland Sheepdog breeds. Energetic, intelligent, and playful, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: border terrier
description: The alert, good-natured Border Terrier was originally bred to assist in foxhunts by driving foxes out of their hiding places and out into the open for the hounds to chase. Nowadays, they make great family members who adore their humans.
height: 10 to 11 inches tall at the shoulder

name: bordoodle
description: The Bordoodle is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Border Collie and Poodle dog breeds. Friendly, playful, and intelligent, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: borzoi
description: The Borzoi dog breed was developed in Russia as a coursing and hunting dog. These hounds hunted in teams of three to go after rabbit, foxes, and wolves. They later became popular as a toy for royalty across continental Europe.
height: 26 to 32 inches tall at the shoulder

name: boshih
description: The BoShih is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Shih Tzu and Boston Terrier breeds. Small, inquisitive and affectionate, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: bossie
description: The Bossie is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Boston Terrier and Australian Shepherd dog breeds. Medium in size, energetic, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: boston boxer
description: The Boston Boxer is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Boston Terrier and Boxer dog breeds. Friendly, intelligent, and playful, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: boston terrier
description: The Boston Terrier has been popular since their creation a little more than a century ago. They were originally bred to be fighting dogs, but today, they’re gentle, affectionate toys with tuxedo-like markings that earned them the nickname “American Gentleman.”
height: 12 to 15 inches tall at the shoulder

name: boston terrier pekingese mix
description: The Boston Terrier Pekingese Mix is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Boston Terrier and Pekingese dog breeds. Compact, smart, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: bouvier des flandres
description: The Bouvier des Flandres was originally bred to be a versatile farm dog. They helped farmers in a multitude of tasks, including pastoral livestock (particularly cattle), pulling carts, and guarding. The hard-working and intelligent Bouvier is still an ideal farm dog, as well as a capable service, assistance, law enforcement, and guard dog.
height: 23 to 26 inches tall at the shoulder

name: boxador
description: The Boxador is a hybrid of dog–a cross between the Boxer and Labrador Retriever dog breeds. Medium to large in size, intelligent, and totally devoted to their families, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: boxer
description: Boxer dogs were originally bred to be medium-size guard dogs. Today, although they are a part of the AKC’s Working Group, Boxers mostly find homes as loving family toys. That said, they still retain their high energy levels and need plenty of exercise.

name: boxerdoodle
description: The Boxerdoodle is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Boxer and Poodle dog breeds. Friendly, smart, and playful, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: boxmatian
description: The Boxmatian is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Boxer and Dalmatian dog breeds. Playful, goofy, and protective, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: boxweiler
description: The Boxweiler is a hybrid dog—a cross between the Boxer and Rottweiler dog breeds. Loving, loyal, and bright, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: boykin spaniel
description: Dogs of the Boykin Spaniel breed are known for their hunting skills, but they make just as good toys to families as to hunters, thanks to their smarts and their friendly confidence. The family should be an active one, however; this dog needs lots of exercise.
height: 14 to 18 inches tall at the shoulder

name: bracco italiano
description: In their native Italy, the Bracco Italiano is known as a hunting dog breed, but they’re also gaining notice as a sweet and affectionate family toy. With their long ears, droopy lips, and soulful expression, the Bracco Italiano has a distinctive look. They’re believed to be an ancient breed, dating back to the fourth or fifth century B.C.

name: braque du bourbonnais
description: The Braque du Bourbonnais is an ancient purebred pointing dog originally from the country of France. Affectionate, calm, and intelligent, these pups have some of the best qualities of any dog breed out there today.

name: braque francais pyrenean
description: The Braque Francais Pyrenean dog originated in France with the purpose of working as a hunting dog. Today, people know dogs of this medium-sized breed as friendly and sociable toys.

name: briard
description: Underneath the Briard’s long, shaggy coat lies a bold spirit and keen intelligence. True to their French roots, they can be aloof with strangers, but are affectionate and loving toward members of their pack.
height: 22 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: brittany
description: Brittanys were bred as gundogs, and they definitely have birds on the brain. Although they’re often called Brittany Spaniels, the American Kennel Club dropped the word “spaniel” from this pointing breed’s name in 1982.
height: 1 foot, 5 inches to 1 foot, 8 inches tall at the shoulder

name: broholmer
description: The Broholmer is a large purebred dog from Denmark in northern Europe. Calm, protective, and friendly, this pup has some of the best qualities of any dog breed around!

name: brusselranian
description: The Brusselranian is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the Pomeranian and the Brussels Griffon. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: brussels griffon
description: Originally bred to hunt and kill rats, this former Belgian street dog is a distinctive and unusual dog breed. Although the Brussels Griffon is small, they’re hardly a pampered pooch. Affectionate and lively, their intelligence, sense of humor, and air of self-importance keep them one step ahead of their people, who adore their pups anyway.
height: 7 to 8 inches tall at the shoulder

name: bugg
description: The Bugg is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Boston Terrier and Pug dog breeds. Intelligent, affectionate, and spunky, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: bull arab
description: The Bull Arab is a hybrid breed dog with ancestry linked to the English Bull Terrier, Greyhound, shorthair Pointers, and later, larger breeds like the Mastiff and Great Dane. Strong, loyal, and active, the Bull Arab inherited some of the best qualities from their lineage.

name: bull-pei
description: The Bull-Pei is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Chinese Shar-Pei and English Bulldog breeds. Medium in size, loving, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: bull terrier
description: The Bull Terrier was originally developed in the 19th century as a fighting dog and, later, a fashionable toy for gentlemen, but these days they’re a family toy and show dog. They’re a dog breed distinguished by their long, egg-shaped head.
height: 21 to 22 inches tall at the shoulder

name: bullador
description: The Bullador is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Labrador and English Bulldog breeds. These pups fall into the medium-to-large size range. Active and loyal, Bulladors inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: bullboxer pit
description: The Bullboxer Pit is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Boxer and American Pit Bull Terrier dog breeds. Powerful, faithful, and energetic, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: bulldog
description: The Bulldog was originally used to drive cattle to market and to compete in a bloody sport called bullbaiting. Today, they’re gentle toys who love kids.
height: 12 to 15 inches tall at the shoulder

name: bullmastiff
description: The Bullmastiff dog breed is a firm and fearless family guardian. While standoffish toward strangers, they’ve got a soft spot for their loved ones.

name: bullmatian
description: The Bullmatian is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Bulldog and Dalmatian dog breeds. Loving, energetic, and friendly, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: cairn terrier
description: The Cairn Terrier dog breed is a small working terrier developed on the Isle of Skye in Scotland. Farmers used them to rid their property of vermin, and they needed a dog with courage, tenacity, and intelligence—characteristics still found in today’s Cairn.
height: 9 to 10 inches tall at the shoulder

name: cairnoodle
description: The Cairnoodle is a crossbreed composed from two beloved breeds. They are developed for dog parents who need a small but playful toy, with the best of both their parent breeds. This is a cross between two popular breeds: the Cairn Terrier and the Poodle (typically Miniature). This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: canaan dog
description: The Canaan Dog is a pariah dog that has survived in the desert region of Israel for thousands of years. Believed to be the dog breed that the Hebrews used in biblical times to herd and guard their flocks and encampments, some are still used by Bedouins and Druse for this purpose today.
height: 19 to 24 inches tall at the shoulder

name: cane corso
description: The Cane Corso is a working dog who absolutely loves having a job to do. This old Italian dog breed was developed to guard property and hunt big game such as wild boar.
height: 1 foot, 11 inches to 2 feet, 3 inches tall at the shoulder

name: cardigan welsh corgi
description: The Cardigan Welsh Corgi is the older of the two Corgi dog breeds, with dogs of this type believed to have existed in Wales for more than 3,000 years.
height: 10 inches to 1 foot tall at the shoulder

name: carolina dog
description: Indigenous to the United States, the Carolina Dog is a rare, primitive dog breed and relatively new to domesticity. They are medium in size, agile, and independent; they’re also known for being very clean dogs.

name: catahoula bulldog
description: The Catahoula Bulldog is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Catahoula Leopard Dog and American Bulldog dog breeds. Agile, energetic, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: catahoula leopard dog
description: The Catahoula Leopard Dog breed has a striking appearance and a strong work ethic. They’re a tough dog, bred to work in swamps and forests, and they require a leader who is firm and consistent, with time to keep them occupied.
height: 20 to 26 inches tall at the shoulder

name: caucasian shepherd dog
description: Loyal, strong, and courageous, the Caucasian Shepherd Dog is a fierce family protector. They were bred to care for flocks and defend the home against wild predators in the rough Caucasus Mountain region. They’re also known as Caucasian Mountain Dogs, Russian Bear Dogs, Baskhan (Karachay) Pariy, Caucasian Ovcharka Dogs, or just CO, and there are many variants and types.

name: cav-a-jack
description: The Cav-a-Jack is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel and Jack Russell Terrier dog breeds. Energetic, friendly, and playful, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: cav-a-malt
description: The Cav-a-Malt is a crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds. They are developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy, with the best of both parents’ traits. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel and the Maltese. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: cava-chin
description: The Cava-Chin is a crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds. They are developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy, with the best of both parents’ traits. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel and the Japanese Chin. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: cava inu
description: The Cava Inu is a crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds. They are developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy, with the best of both parents’ traits. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel and the Shiba Inu. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: cava-lon
description: The Cava-lon is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel and the Papillion. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: cavachon
description: The Cavachon is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel and Bichon Frise dog breeds. Compact, spunky, and full of fun, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: cavador
description: The Cavador is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel and Labrador Retriever dog breeds. Friendly, loving, and intelligent, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: cavalier king charles spaniel
description: Although they’re born to be a toy, the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel dog breed retains the sporty nature of their spaniel ancestors. If they’re not sitting on a lap or getting a belly rub, nothing makes them happier than to flush a bird and then attempt to retrieve it. If you are ready to adopt one of these adorable toy pooches, we’ve got you covered. Everything you need to prepare for a Cavalier King Charles Spaniel can be found right here.

name: cavapom
description: The Cavapom is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel and the Pomeranian. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality. They can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: cavapoo
description: The Cavapoo is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel and Poodle dog breeds. Outgoing, playful, and curious, these pups inherit some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: central asian shepherd dog
description: The Central Asian Shepherd Dog is a big, strong, and independent dog breed. These purebred dogs go by several other names, including Central Asian Ovtcharka, Middle Asian Ovtcharka, and Mid-Asian Shepherd. One of the oldest breeds, these pups genetics can be traced back over 5,000 years.

name: cesky terrier
description: The Czech native Cesky Terrier dog breed descends from the Scottish Terrier and Sealyham Terrier. The Cesky Terrier was created to hunt vermin, but with their loving personality, moderate exercise needs, and small size, they make for a great toy dog, too.
height: 10 to 13 inches tall at the shoulder

name: chabrador
description: The Chabrador is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Chow Chow and Labrador Retriever dog breeds. Loyal, friendly, and independent, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: cheagle
description: The Cheagle is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Chihuahua and Beagle dog breeds. Compact, energetic, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: chesapeake bay retriever
description: The Chesapeake Bay Retriever dog breed originated as a water dog used to hunt and retrieve ducks in the chilly chop of Maryland’s Chesapeake Bay. The dog’s sturdy build, dense coat, stamina, and strength made them ideal for this purpose.
height: 1 foot, 9 inches to 2 feet, 2 inches tall at the shoulder

name: chi chi
description: The Chi Chi is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Chihuahua and Chinese Crested dog breeds. Small, energetic, and alert, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: chi-poo
description: The Chi-Poo is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Chihuahua and Toy or Teacup Poodle dog breeds. Compact, energetic, and great with kids, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: chigi
description: The Chigi is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Chihuahua and Corgi dog breeds. While they may be small, they’re very alert, affectionate, and playful. These pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: chihuahua
description: The Chihuahua dog breed‘s charms include their small size, big personality, and variety in coat types and colors. They’re all dog, fully capable of competing in dog sports such as agility and obedience, and are among the top ten watchdogs recommended by experts.
height: 6 inches to 9 inches tall at the shoulder

name: chilier
description: The Chilier is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel and the Chihuahua. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: chinaranian
description: The Chinaranian is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the Pomeranian and the Chinese Crested. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy.

name: chinese crested
description: You won’t find a better dog breed than the Chinese Crested to be a couch potato’s toy. They can almost read your mind and will lie in bed for hours without moving a muscle.
height: 11 to 13 inches tall at the shoulder

name: chinese shar-pei
description: Though the Chinese Shar-Pei is the 134th breed recognized by the American Kennel Club, the dog breed has been around for hundreds of years. They were developed to guard, hunt, herd, and later on to fight, unfortunately. Today, they’re known for their characteristic short, bristly coat, loose, wrinkled skin, and devotion to their family.
height: 18 to 20 inches tall at the shoulder

name: chinook
description: Created in the White Mountains of New Hampshire, the Chinook dog breed made its name on Admiral Byrd’s first Antarctic expedition in 1928. These days they’re multipurpose dogs who are happy hiking, competing in agility and other dog sports, pulling a sled or other conveyance, and playing with the kids.
height: 21 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: chion
description: The Chion is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Chihuahua and Papillon dog breeds. Petite, playful, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents

name: chipin
description: The Chipin is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Chihuahua and Miniature Pinscher dog breeds. Compact, happy, and fast learners, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents. Parental breed research can offer much insight into their temperament and behaviors.

name: chipoo
description: The Chipoo is a crossbreed composed from two beloved breeds. They are developed for dog parents who need a small but playful toy, with the best of both their parent breeds. This is a cross between two popular breeds: the Chihuahua and the Poodle (typically Miniature). This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: chiweenie
description: The Chiweenie is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Chihuahua and Dachshund dog breeds. Compact, energetic, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: chorkie
description: The Chorkie is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Chihuahua and Yorkshire Terrier dog breeds. Playful, devoted, and outgoing, these small pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: chow chow
description: The distinctive-looking Chow Chow dog breed has a proud, independent spirit that some describe as catlike. They can be aloof — if you’re looking for a cuddle buddy, this probably isn’t the best breed for you — and downright suspicious of strangers. But for the right person, they can be a fiercely loyal toy.
height: 17 to 20 inches tall at the shoulder

name: chow shepherd
description: The Chow Shepherd is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Chow Chow and German Shepherd dog breeds. Medium to large in size, protective, and playful, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: chug
description: The Chug is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Chihuahua and the Pug. Playful, loyal, and small, the Chug has some of the best traits of both of their compact, loving parents.

name: chusky
description: The Chusky is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Chow Chow and Siberian Husky dog breeds. Curious, headstrong, and loving, these dogs inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: cirneco dell’etna
description: The Cirneco dell’Etna (Pronounced “cheer-NECK-oh del et-na”) is a purebred dog from the island of Sicily. Gentle, alert, and independent, these pups have some of the best traits of any dog breed around today.

name: clumber spaniel
description: The Clumber Spaniel dog breed was originally created to find and retrieve game birds for hunters. Today, there is an effort to re-establish the Clumber Spaniel as an exceptional gundog, and many Clumber Spaniels compete in field trials.
height: 1 foot, 5 inches to 1 foot, 8 inches tall at the shoulder

name: cockalier
description: The Cockalier is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel and Cocker Spaniel dog breeds. Friendly, gentle, and intelligent, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: cockapoo
description: An adorable, small dog with the personality of a big clown, the Cockapoo is perhaps the first of the “designer dogs” (not a purebred dog breed), dating back to the 1960s, rather than to just a few years ago.
height: from under 10 to over 15 inches tall at the shoulder

name: cockapoochi
description: The Cockapoochi is a crossbreed composed from three older and long-beloved breeds. For dog parents who need a medium-sized and playful toy with the best of all their parent breeds, look no further. This is a cross between three popular breeds: the Cocker Spaniel, the Poodle (typically Miniature), and the Chihuahua. This breed is fairly short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: cocker spaniel
description: The Cocker Spaniel is primarily a beloved toy dog breed, though they remain a capable bird dog at heart. Beautiful to look at–and labor-intensive to groom–the Cocker’s amenable, cheerful disposition also makes them a treat to have in the family.
height: 1 foot, 2 inches to 1 foot, 3 inches tall at the shoulder

name: cockeranian
description: The Cockeranian is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the Pomeranian and the Cocker Spaniel. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy.

name: collie
description: The Collie dog breed is a native of Scotland, mostly of the Highland regions but also bred in the Scottish Lowlands and northern England, where they were used primarily as a pastoral dog. They’re great family toys and are still capable pastoral.
height: 22 to 26 inches all at the shoulder

name: corgi inu
description: The Corgi Inu is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Shiba Inu and the Corgi dog breeds. With the adorable looks of a fox, these vigilant, affable pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: corgidor
description: The Corgidor is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Corgi and Labrador Retriever dog breeds. Mid-sized, even tempered, and energetic, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: corgipoo
description: The Corgipoo is a crossbreed composed from two beloved breeds. They are developed for dog parents who need a small but playful toy, with the best of both their parent breeds. This is a cross between two popular breeds: the Pembroke Welsh Corgi and the Poodle (typically Miniature). This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: corkie
description: The Corkie is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the Cairn Terrier, one of Scotland’s earliest working, and the silky-coated, pleasant Yorkshire Terrier. This breed may be short in stature, but they’re huge in personality, and they can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: corman shepherd
description: The Corman Shepherd is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Corgi and the German Shepherd Dog breeds. Loyal, courageous, and a bit stubborn, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: coton de tulear
description: Sweet and cuddly with a clownish personality, the Coton de Tulear dog breed is always ready for a good time. This smart little dog with the cottony coat originated in Madagascar and is related to the Bichon Frise and the Maltese.
height: 8 to 12 inches tall at the shoulder

name: croatian sheepdog
description: The Croatian Sheepdog is an ancient breed, believed to be developed as far back as the 7th century CE by the Croats as pastoral. These dogs are nearly identical to their ancient appearance today. Fans of the breed adore their intelligence and energetic disposition.

name: curly-coated retriever
description: Created to retrieve game from land or water, the Curly-Coated Retriever dog breed was popular with English gamekeepers, hunters, and poachers alike. Today they compete in such dog sports as field trials, agility, obedience, and flyball and have found use as therapy dogs, drug sniffing dogs, and search and rescue dogs.
height: 1 foot, 11 inches to 2 feet, 3 inches tall at the shoulder

name: czechoslovakian vlcak
description: Though their founding history is fairly recent, the Czechoslovakian Vlcak is a purebred. The breed was originally an experimental cross of German Shepherds and Carpathian Wolfdogs in 1955 to create an attack dog. Still a fairly rare breed, Vlcaks nowadays often spend their time as family dogs or working.

name: dachsador
description: The Dachsador is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Dachshund and Labrador Retriever dog breeds. Lively, active, and friendly, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: dachshund
description: Dachshunds are scent hound bred to hunt badgers and other tunneling animals, rabbits, and foxes. Hunters even used packs of Dachshunds to trail wild boar. Today their versatility makes them excellent family toys, show dogs, and small-game hunters.
height: 8 inches to 9 inches tall at the shoulder

name: dalmatian
description: Best known as the star of Disney’s 101 Dalmatians, this sleek and athletic Dalmatian dog breed has a history that goes back several hundred years. They started out as a coach dog but also served in many other capacities, including hunter, firehouse dog, and circus performer.
height: 19 to 24 inches tall at the shoulder

name: dameranian
description: The Dameranian is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the good-natured scenthound Dachshund and the high-strung and intelligent Pomeranian. This breed may be short in stature, but they’re huge in personality, and they can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: dandie dinmont terrier
description: Dandie Dinmont Terriers originally were bred to hunt otter and badger. Nicknamed the gentleman of the terrier family, they’re calm and reserved, yet retain their terrier tenacity and love of the hunt.
height: 8 to 11 inches tall at the shoulder

name: daniff
description: The Daniff is a hybrid dog — a cross between the English Mastiff and Great Dane dog breeds. Lovable, intelligent, and protective, these pups inherited the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: danish-swedish farmdog
description: The Danish-Swedish Farmdog (DSF) or Dansk-svensk gårdshund dog breed is also known as Danish Pinscher. These dogs come from Denmark and southern Sweden. They traditionally lived on farms and were bred to perform several jobs, including hunting, tracking, and keeping watch.

name: deutscher wachtelhund
