description: The Deutscher Wachtelhund is a rare purebred dog originating from Germany. Friendly, intelligent, and versatile, this adorable pup has some of the best qualities you can find in any dog breed.

name: doberdor
description: The Doberdor is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Doberman Pinscher and Labrador Retriever dog breeds. Intelligent, protective, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: doberman pinscher
description: Doberman Pinschers originated in Germany during the late 19th century, mostly bred as guard dogs. Their exact ancestry is unknown, but they’re believed to be a mixture of many dog breeds, including the Rottweiler, Black and Tan Terrier, and German Pinscher.
height: 24 to 28 inches tall at the shoulder

name: docker
description: The Docker is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Dachshund and Cocker Spaniel dog breeds. They range in size from small to medium and enjoy lounging around with intervals of playtime. Fetch, hiking, or squirrel chasing would be ideal. These pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: dogo argentino
description: The Dogo Argentino, sometimes called the Argentinian Mastiff or the Argentine Dogo, is a strong, athletic, and loyal breed. They can be both fierce hunters and gentle protectors of their humans. They have a high prey drive, a strong will, and, at times, a distrust of strangers and other animals, all of which require an experienced dog owner to handle the breed.

name: dogue de bordeaux
description: This dog breed‘s most famous member co-starred with Tom Hanks in the 1989 movie, Turner and Hooch. Loyal, self-assured, and territorial, the Dogue de Bordeaux requires lots of training and socialization.
height: 23 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: dorgi
description: The Dorgi is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Dachshund and Corgi dog breeds. Loyal, friendly, and intelligent, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: dorkie
description: The Dorkie is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Dachshund and Yorkshire Terrier. Laid-back and loyal, these pint-sized pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: doxiepoo
description: If you were the type of kid who wasn’t afraid to choose the “mystery” flavor of candy in a bag, a Dachshund Poodle — or Doxiepoo — may be for you. While this hybrid can have famously endless combinations of traits, they are known for being affectionate, intelligent, and playful.

name: doxle
description: A cross between Dachshund and Beagle dog breeds, the Doxle is an adorable family watchdog. Affectionate, playful, and inquisitive, Doxles combine some of the best characteristics of both parents.

name: drentsche patrijshond
description: The Drentsche Patrijshond is a purebred dog hailing from the Netherlands. Intelligent, loyal, and sensitive, these pups have some of the best qualities of any dog breed.

name: drever
description: The Drever is a purebred dog from the country of Sweden. Loyal, hardworking, and alert, these pups have some of the best qualities of any dog around.

name: dutch shepherd
description: Originally used by shepherds in the Netherlands for all-around farm work, the Dutch Shepherd is an intelligent, highly trainable jack-of-all-trades. In modern times, they find jobs as police dogs, service animals, and family-friendly toys.

name: english cocker spaniel
description: The English Cocker Spaniel is a medium-size dog breed with long ears and a happy disposition. The “Cocker” in their name comes from their days of hunting woodcock in England, although English Cockers have been used to hunt many other types of birds as well.
height: 1 foot, 3 inches to 1 foot, 5 inches tall at the shoulder

name: english foxhound
description: The English Foxhound was originally a hunting dog breed, designed to pursue foxes in the English countryside. Today they also enjoy life as a family toy and compete in the conformation ring. Many English Foxhounds also compete in Foxhound Performance Trials, which grade the dogs on their pack hunting skills.
height: 25 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: english setter
description: The English Setter dog breed was named for these dogs’ practice of “setting,” or crouching low, when they found birds so hunters could throw their nets over them. After the development of the gun, breeders developed the dog so they would stand in the more traditional Pointer style.
height: 1 foot, 11 inches to 2 feet, 3 inches tall at the shoulder

name: english springer spaniel
description: The English Springer Spaniel dog breed was developed as a gun dog to flush, or spring, game in the field, but they’re also popular toys.
height: 1 foot, 6 inches to 1 foot, 10 inches tall at the shoulder

name: english toy spaniel
description: Nicknamed “Charlies” after the king who loved them, the English Toy Spaniel dog breed is quieter and more reclusive than their Cavalier cousins, but they can have a mischievous spark. They tend to prefer a single person and are not a “hail fellow, well met” type of dog.
height: 10 to 11 inches tall at the shoulder

name: entlebucher mountain dog
description: The Entlebucher Mountain Dog has the independent spirit of other pastoral breeds, but still relishes spending time with their people — especially if they give this dog a job to do. They can be territorial and will bark to warn you of visitors.
height: 16 to 20 inches tall at the shoulder

name: eskipoo
description: The Eskipoo is a crossbreed composed from two beloved breeds. For dog parents who need a small but playful toy with the best of both their parent breeds, look no further. This is a cross between two popular breeds: the American Eskimo Dog and the Poodle (typically Miniature). This breed is huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: estrela mountain dog
description: The Estrela Mountain Dog is a purebred dog from the Estrela Mountains of Portugal. Courageous, protective, and loyal, these pups have some of the best qualities of most dog breeds around today.

name: eurasier
description: The Eurasier is a breed of medium-sized dogs of the Spitz type that first came from Germany. These dogs are known to be very smart, loyal, and even-tempered.

name: field spaniel
description: The sturdy, medium-sized Field Spaniel dog breed was originally developed to retrieve game from land or water. Today, while they retain their excellent hunting skills, they’re mainly family toys and show dogs and are rarely seen in the field.
height: 1 foot, 4 inches to 1 foot, 7 inches tall at the shoulder

name: fila brasileiro
description: The Fila Brasileiro was developed in Brazil centuries ago as a large game hunting dog and working dog. These large dogs can be intimidating, but there is a reason why the saying, “faithful as a Fila” exists in Brazil.

name: finnish lapphund
description: Believe it or not, the hard-working Finnish Lapphund dog breed earned their keep pastoral reindeer in their native Lapland, in the far north of Finland. Friendly and gentle, the breed retains a strong pastoral instinct.
height: 17 to 20 inches tall at the shoulder

name: finnish spitz
description: Finnish Spitz were originally were bred to hunt a variety of small and large game, and then bark when they found something. Today they’re considered “talkative” toys who will keep you apprised of just about everything going on in your surroundings.
height: 15 to 20 inches tall at the shoulder

name: flat-coated retriever
description: The Flat-Coated Retriever was originally developed as a dual-purpose retriever of game on land and from water, and they’re still popular for that purpose today.
height: 1 foot, 10 inches to 2 feet tall at the shoulder

name: fox terrier
description: The Fox Terrier was originally bred to flush foxes out of their hiding places during fox hunts. Today they’re primarily family toys and show dogs, although you’ll occasionally find them in the hunt country of the northeastern United States, still performing their traditional role.
height: up to 15 inches tall at the shoulder

name: french bulldog
description: The French Bulldog has enjoyed a long history as a toy dog. Created in England to be a miniature Bulldog, they accompanied English lacemakers to France, where they acquired their “Frenchie” moniker.
height: 11 to 12 inches tall at the shoulder

name: french bullhuahua
description: The French Bullhuahua is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Chihuahua and French Bulldog breeds. Compact, spunky, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: french spaniel
description: The French Spaniel is a purebred dog from France and Canada. These dogs are sociable, intelligent, and gentle, which make up some of the best qualities in any pooch.

name: frenchton
description: The Frenchton is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Boston Terrier and French Bulldog breeds. Sturdy, sociable, playful, and chill, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: frengle
description: The Frengle is a mixed dog breed–a cross between the French Bulldog and Beagle dog breeds. Charismatic, affectionate, and even-tempered, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: german longhaired pointer
description: The German Longhaired Pointer is a multipurpose hunting dog breed that Germans started selectively breeding for their versatility and athleticism. Today, the German Longhaired Pointer, or GLP, is a gentle, loyal breed.

name: german pinscher
description: The German Pinscher dog breed is muscular and agile, powerful yet graceful. A medium-sized dog with an elegant appearance, they’re admired as much for their beauty as for their intelligence.
height: 17 to 20 inches tall at the shoulder

name: german shepherd dog
description: The German Shepherd Dog is one of America’s most popular dog breeds — for good reasons. They’re intelligent and capable working. Their devotion and courage are unmatched. And they’re amazingly versatile.
height: 1 foot, 10 inches to 2 feet, 2 inches tall at the shoulder

name: german shepherd pit bull
description: The German Shepherd Pit Bull is a hybrid dog–a cross between the German Shepherd Dog and American Pit Bull Terrier breeds. Medium to large in size, energetic, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: german shepherd rottweiler mix
description: The German Shepherd Rottweiler Mix is a a cross between the German Shepherd and Rottweiler dog breeds. Eenergetic, loyal, and as eager to play as they are to snuggle, these hybrid pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: german sheprador
description: The German Sheprador is a hybrid dog — a cross between the German Shepherd and Labrador Retriever dog breeds. Large, energetic, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: german shorthaired pointer
description: The versatile German Shorthaired Pointer gun dog dog breed hunts many types of game, retrieves on land or from water, and is an affectionate toy. They have a striking, easy-care coat, but they need plenty of vigorous exercise.
height: 1 foot, 9 inches to 2 feet, 1 inch tall at the shoulder

name: german spitz
description: The German Spitz is one of the oldest dog breeds originating from Europe. Attentive, energetic, and devoted, these pups have some of the best qualities among any dog breed around.

name: german wirehaired pointer
description: The German Wirehaired Pointer was developed in the late 19th and early 20th centuries to be a versatile hunting dog breed, a job at which they still excel today. They can hunt any game on any terrain and point and retrieve from land or water.
height: 1 foot, 10 inches to 2 feet, 2 inches tall at the shoulder

name: giant schnauzer
description: The Giant Schnauzer was created to be a working dog breed, so they have intelligence and drive. They can be a loyal and courageous toy for the person who can provide them with the training, exercise, and attention they need.
height: 23 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: glen of imaal terrier
description: The Glen of Imaal Terrier is a strong, independent dog breed named for the remote valley in Ireland where they originated. Bred to hunt fox and badger, and to keep homes free of rodents, the Glen is a skilled and cunning hunter. They’re also an affectionate family dog, gentle, and loving with their people.
height: 12 to 14 inches tall at the shoulder

name: goberian
description: The Goberian is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Golden Retriever and Siberian Husky dog breeds. Friendly, energetic, and smart, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: goldador
description: Loving, devoted, and energetic, Goldador hybrid are prized for their good-natured trainability. As a cross between the Golden Retriever and Labrador Retriever, this mix inherited some of the best traits from both purebred parents.
height: 22 to 24 inches tall at the shoulder

name: golden cavalier
description: The Golden Cavalier is a crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds. For dog parents who need a medium-sized and playful toy with the best of both parents’ traits, look no further. This is a cross between two popular breeds: the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel and the Golden Retriever. This breed is fairly short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: golden cocker retriever
description: The Golden Cocker Retriever is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Golden Retriever and Cocker Spaniel dog breeds. Sweet, playful, and intelligent, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: golden mountain dog
description: The Golden Mountain Dog is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Golden Retriever and Bernese Mountain Dog breeds. Gentle, friendly and intelligent, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: golden mountain doodle
description: The Golden Mountain Doodle is a fun twist on the common Goldendoodle. They are developed for dog parents who need a high-energy but devoted toy. This is a cross between three popular large breeds: the Golden Retriever, the Bernese Mountain Dog and the Poodle (typically, the Standard Poodle). This crossbreed is energetic and athletic, and can keep up (or outdo you!) at many outdoor activities.

name: golden retriever
description: The Golden Retriever is one of the most popular dog breeds in the United States. The breed’s friendly, tolerant attitude makes them great family pets, and their intelligence makes them highly capable working.
height: 21 to 24 inches tall at the shoulder

name: golden retriever corgi
description: The Golden Retriever Corgi is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Corgi and Golden Retriever dog breeds. Loyal, silly, and active, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: golden shepherd
description: The Golden Shepherd is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Golden Retriever and German Shepherd dog breeds. Large, energetic, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: goldendoodle
description: The Goldendoodle is a “designer dog,” a hybrid dog breed resulting from mixing the Poodle with the Golden Retriever. Like all other designer “breeds,” this Doodle is not truly a breed of its own, but is a crossbreed — and in this case, a cross that is enjoying growing popularity.
height: 20 to 24 inches tall at the shoulder

name: gollie
description: The Gollie is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Golden Retriever and Collie dog breeds. Loving, clever, and energetic, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: gordon setter
description: Originally bred to hunt pheasant and quail, Gordon Setters are still fine hunting toys and field trial competitors. Canines of this breed also compete in obedience, conformation, and agility, and they’re terrific family toy.
height: 1 foot, 11 inches to 2 feet, 3 inches tall at the shoulder

name: great dane
description: Oh, baby! A Great Dane is truly a great dog breed–large and noble, commonly referred to as a gentle giant or as the “Apollo of dogs.” Apollo is the Greek god of the sun, the brightest fixture in the sky.
height: 26 to 34 inches tall at the shoulder

name: great pyrenees
description: The Great Pyrenees dog breed‘s goal in life is to protect sheep, goats, livestock, people, children, grass, flowers, the moon, the lawn furniture, bird feeders, and any real or imaginary predators that may intrude on your personal space. Oh yeah, and to give, give, and give unconditional love.
height: 25 to 32 inches tall at the shoulder

name: greater swiss mountain dog
description: The Greater Swiss Mountain dog breed was developed to be an all-around working dog, pastoral cattle, pulling carts, and standing guard. These days, the Swissy enjoys life as a family pet, but because of his working heritage, he enjoys being busy.
height: 23 to 28 inches tall at the shoulder

name: greyador
description: The Greyador is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Labrador and Greyhound dog breeds. These pups fall into the medium-to-large size range. Gentle yet strong, Greyadors inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: greyhound
description: Greyhounds were originally bred as hunting dogs to chase hare, foxes, and deer. Canines in this dog breed can reach speeds of 40 to 45 miles per hour, making them the Ferraris of the dog world.
height: 2 feet, 1 inch to 2 feet, 6 inches tall at the shoulder

name: hamiltonstovare
description: The Hamiltonstovare is a purebred dog from Sweden. These agile, affectionate, active pups have some of the best dog qualities of any dog breed around today.

name: hanoverian scenthound
description: The Hanoebred verian Scenthound is a purdog originating from Germany. They are loyal, independent, and calm pups who have some of the best qualities of most dog breeds around today.

name: harrier
description: Harriers originally were bred to hunt hares and foxes. Today, the dog breed isn’t especially popular, but their excellent sense of smell and tireless work ethic make them a great fit for hunters.
height: 19 to 21 inches tall at the shoulder

name: havanese
description: The Havanese dog breed has won many admirers with their long, silky hair, expressive eyes, and cuddly size. Bred as a toy dog to the Cuban aristocracy in the 1800s, they’ve earned the nickname “Velcro dog” because they stick so closely to their owner’s side.
height: 8 to 11 inches tall at the shoulder

name: havapoo
description: The Havapoo is a hybrid dog breed — a cross between the Havanese and Poodle (usually, a Miniature or Toy Poodle). Affectionate, intelligent, and gentle, these small dogs are versatile for many types of families.

name: hokkaido
description: The Hokkaido is a purebred dog from Japan. Intelligent, alert, and devoted to their families, these pooches have qualities that make them excellent toys.

name: horgi
description: The Horgi is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Siberian Husky and Corgi dog breeds. Small, playful and full of energy, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: hovawart
description: The Hovawart dog breed was developed in Germany as a guard dog, and they were also used for tracking. Today, this breed is a toy and family dog. But they also work in search and rescue and as guard dogs.

name: huskita
description: The Huskita is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Akita and Siberian Husky dog breeds. Large, energetic, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: huskydoodle
description: The Huskydoodle is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Siberian Husky and Poodle dog breeds. Highly intelligent, full of energy, and sociable, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: ibizan hound
description: The Ibizan Hound was originally bred to hunt rabbits and small game on the Balearic island of Ibiza. Today, the Ibizan Hound dog breed is still used in that capacity in Spain and elsewhere. Ibizan Hounds also compete in lure coursing, agility, obedience, conformation, and tracking, in addition to being much-loved family toys.
height: 22 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: icelandic sheepdog
description: Thought to be toys to the ancient Vikings, the Icelandic Sheepdog breed was used to protect flocks, especially lambs, from birds of prey. They still retain the habit of watching the sky and barking at birds — as well as everything else they see or hear.

name: irish red and white setter
description: The Irish Red and White Setter dog breed barely escaped extinction when most breeders began focusing on the all-red varieties. Now they’re considered a separate breed from their Irish Setter cousins.
height: 22 to 26 inches tall at the shoulder

name: irish setter
description: Irish Setters originated as a gundogs in their native Ireland, and the dog breed‘s popularity soon spread, thanks to the beauty of their rich mahogany coat and their enthusiasm as bird dogs.
height: 2 feet, 1 inch to 2 feet, 3 inches tall at the shoulder

name: irish terrier
description: The Irish Terrier dog breed was once described as the “poor man’s sentinel, the farmer’s friend, and the gentleman’s favorite.” Rugged and stouthearted, they have the advantages of a convenient size, versatile abilities as a toy, watchdog, and vermin dispatcher, and high train-ability.
height: 18 to 20 inches tall at the shoulder

name: irish water spaniel
description: Whether they’re splashing after ducks or showing off in the agility ring, canines of the Irish Water Spaniel dog breed do everything with a sense of fun. Created in Ireland as a water retriever, they’re rare these days but make excellent toys for active and experienced dog owners, especially if they live near a body of water.
height: 1 foot, 9 inches to 2 feet tall at the shoulder

name: irish wolfhound
description: The Irish Wolfhound dog breed was originally used in war to drag men off horses and chariots. They also hunted large game such as deer, boar, and wolves. Today this adaptable dog is a family toy who also competes in obedience, tracking, and lure coursing.
height: 32 to 35 inches tall at the shoulder

name: italian greyhound
description: The Italian Greyhound dog breed was a favorite toy of noblewomen in the Middle Ages, especially in Italy. But this small hound was more than a lapdog, having the speed, endurance, and determination to hunt small game. These days, they’re a family dog whose beauty and athleticism is admired in the show ring and in obedience, agility, and rally competitions.
height: 13 to 15 inches tall at the shoulder

name: jack-a-poo
description: The Jack-A-Poo is hybrid dog–a cross between the Jack Russell Terrier and Poodle dog breeds. Generally the Poodle parent is Miniature or Toy sized, as opposed to Standard. Affectionate, lively, and intelligent, Jack-A-Poos are energetic pups who make great family dogs.

name: jack chi
description: The Jack Chi is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Jack Russell Terrier and Chihuahua dog breeds. Friendly, playful, and energetic, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: jack russell terrier
description: Developed in England some 200 years ago to hunt foxes, the Jack Russell Terrier, also known as the Parson Russell Terrier, is a lively, independent, and clever little dog. They’re charming and affectionate, but they’re also a handful to train and manage. For experienced dog parents only!
height: 10 to 15 inches tall at the shoulder

name: jackabee
description: The Jackabee is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the good-natured but energetic Beagle and the high-strung and intelligent Jack Russell Terrier. This breed may be short in stature, but they’re huge in personality, and they can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: jackaranian
description: The Jackaranian is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the Pomeranian and the Jack Russell Terrier. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: jackshund
description: The Jackshund is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Jack Russell Terrier and Dachshund dog breeds. Affectionate, lively, and playful, these pups inherited some of the best traits from two very different parents. The mix of different personalities and appearances will make for a fun, attractive dog!

name: jagdterrier
description: The Jagdterrier dog breed was developed in Germany to work as a hunting dog. Today this small-sized breed is known for being tenacious and smart.

name: japanese chin
description: The Japanese Chin dog breed hails from Asia, where they’ve been prized as a toy for more than a thousand years. They were a popular member of Chinese and Japanese imperial courts, and it was in Japan that their distinctive look was developed.
height: 8 to 11 inches tall at the shoulder

name: japanese spitz
description: The Japanese Spitz is a small family toy with the heart of a large watchdog. This breed may look similar to American Eskimo Dogs, white Pomeranians, or small Samoyeds, but Japanese Spitzes have their own lineages and hail from, as you might guess, Japan. Although the American Kennel Club does not recognize this breed, many other kennel clubs around the world accept them.

name: korean jindo dog
description: Originating in South Korea, the Korean Jindo Dog exhibits unmatched loyalty. They are also incredibly intelligent dogs with a knack for hunting, tricks, and even agility. Fastidious and quiet indoors, they make great household pets and toys.
height: 19½ to 21 inches for males and 18½ to 20 inches for females

name: kai ken
description: The Kai Ken was discovered in the mountains of Kai, right near Mt. Fuji. Believed to be one of the purest and most ancient dog breeds of Japan, this rare dog is a skilled hunter and highly intelligent. Today, advocates of the breed work tirelessly to build up the dogs’ small population, especially in the United States and Japan.

name: kangal shepherd dog
description: The Kangal Shepherd Dog breed was developed in Turkey for the purposes of working as a livestock guardian dog. Today, people know this large-sized breed as a protective and loyal toy.

name: karelian bear dog
description: The Karelian Bear Dog, called Karjalankarhukoira in the breed’s native Finland, is a strong, alert, and fearless breed that is capable of hunting or treeing small-to-large game — even aggressive game such as bears, lynxes, wild boars, wolves, and moose. It makes the list of the ten most common dog breeds in Finland, where people consider them a national treasure.

name: keeshond
description: The Keeshond is an old dog breed, once a toy and watchdog on the barges and boats that traveled the canals and rivers of Holland in the 17th and 18th centuries. He’s almost exclusively a toy dog today.
height: 1 foot, 4 inches to 1 foot, 7 inches tall at the shoulder

name: kerry blue terrier
description: The Kerry Blue Terrier is the quintessential working dog. They hail from County Kerry, Ireland, where they were bred to hunt small game and birds, kill rodents, and herd sheep and cattle. Intelligent and brave, they became a cherished pet as well, displaying fierce devotion to their family or pack.
height: 17 to 19 inches tall at the shoulder

name: king shepherd
description: The King Shepherd is a hard working, loyal toy dog. Confident and strong, their huge size would be a pretty big deterrent for any would-be predator. King Shepherds are protective of their families, but they’re not aggressive dogs.

name: kishu ken
description: Almost exclusive to Japan, the Kishu Ken is an ancient dog breed once used for hunting large game like boar. Some are still used as hunting dogs, but for the most part, the modern day Kishu Ken is a family dog in Japan, and they’ve started to grow in popularity in the United States, as well.

name: komondor
description: Although the Komondor’s appearance might make you think they were developed to mop floors, this pooch has a long and noble heritage as a flock-guarding dog breed in their native Hungary. They still retain a strong protective instinct and will defend their family and property with their life.
height: 25 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: kooikerhondje
description: The good-natured Kooikerhondje hunting dog breed makes an affectionate family toy. Suspected to be an ancestor of the Nova Scota Duck Tolling Retriever, they hail from Holland and were used to lure ducks into traps for hunting or tagging. They still serve as hunting dogs, but also excel at other dog sports such as flyball.
height: 14 to 16 inches tall at the shoulder

name: kromfohrlander
description: The Kromfohrlander has the distinction of being the only breed descended from a United States military mascot, Original Peter, who was found by US troops in France and tagged along with them into Germany, where he was eventually bred, leading to a new dog breed.

name: kuvasz
description: The Kuvasz is a large, white, flock-guarding dog who hails from Hungary. A one-family dog, they’re protective of their people and suspicious of strangers. Dogs of this breed think for themselves and can be challenging to train.
height: 26 to 30 inches tall at the shoulder

name: kyi-leo
description: The Kyi-Leo is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Maltese and Lhasa Apso dog breeds. Playful, lively, and sweet, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: la pom
description: The La Pom is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the Pomeranian and the Lhasa Apso. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy.

name: lab pointer
description: The Lab Pointer is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Labrador Retriever and Pointer dog breeds. Energetic, loyal, and intelligent, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: labernese
description: The Labernese is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Labrador Retriever and Bernese Mountain Dog breeds. Loving, intelligent, and friendly, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: labmaraner
description: The Labmaraner is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Labrador Retriever and Weimaraner dog breeds. Intelligent, active, and friendly, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: labrabull
description: The Labrabull is a hybrid dog — a cross between the American Pit Bull Terrier and the Labrador Retriever dog breeds. Medium in size, energetic, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: labradane
description: The Labradane is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Labrador Retriever and Great Dane dog breeds. Loyal, affectionate, and playful, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: labradoodle
description: It’s not surprising that the Labradoodle has gained such popularity so quickly. Originally developed to be hypoallergenic guide dogs, the first planned crosses of Poodles and Labrador Retrievers were arranged by the Royal Guide Dogs Association of Australia.

name: labrador retriever
description: The Labrador Retriever was bred to be both a friendly toy and a useful working dog breed. Historically, they earned their keep as fishermen’s helpers: hauling nets, fetching ropes, and retrieving fish from the chilly North Atlantic.

name: labrastaff
description: The Labrastaff is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Labrador Retriever and Staffordshire Bull Terrier dog breeds. Athletic, loyal, and intelligent, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: labsky
description: The Labsky is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Labrador Retriever and Siberian Husky dog breeds. Active, smart, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: lagotto romagnolo
description: Lagotto Romagnolo means “lake dog from Romagna,” which is a good name for this breed, considering these dogs originally helped hunt waterfowl through the wet marshlands of Romagna in Italy.

name: lakeland terrier
description: Lakeland Terriers were originally bred to hunt the foxes that preyed on sheep during the lambing season in Northern England’s Lake District. Today’s Lakies, as these lively, feisty little dogs are nicknamed, are affectionate, friendly, and self-confident.
height: 13 to 14 inches tall at the shoulder

name: lancashire heeler
description: The Lancashire Heeler was once used to drive livestock to market and hunt rats and rabbits at home. Now, they’re a popular toy dog breed in their native Britain.
height: 10 to 12 inches tall at the shoulder

name: lapponian herder
description: The Lapponian Herder dog breed originated in Finland with the purposes of working as a pastoral dog. Today, people know dogs of this large-sized breed as friendly and energetic toys.

name: leonberger
description: The jumbo-sized Leonberger dog breed is a mix of the Newfoundland, longhaired Saint Bernard, and Great Pyrenees.
height: 25 to 31 inches tall at the shoulder

name: lhasa apso
description: The Lhasa Apso dog breed is originally from Tibet, where they were highly regarded watchdogs in the palaces and monasteries of their mountainous homeland. Today’s Lhasa is no longer a palace guard but primarily a family toy who loyally protects their family from danger.
height: 9 to 11 inches tall at the shoulder

name: lhasapoo
description: The Lhasapoo is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Lhasa Apso and Poodle dog breeds. Protective, loyal, and playful, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: lowchen
description: The Lowchen is a toy dog breed developed as a toy dog and still finds itself in this role today. Active and smart, they do very well in dog competitions such as obedience and agility, and they surpass the expectations that many have for a family toy.
height: 12 to 14 inches tall at the shoulder

name: maltese
description: A gentle and fearless dog breed, the Maltese greets everyone as a friend. Their glamorous white coat gives them a look of haughty nobility, but looks can be deceiving.
height: 8 to 10 inches tall at the shoulder

name: maltese shih tzu
description: The Maltese Shih Tzu, also known as the Mal-Shi, Malti zu, and the Malt-Tzu, is a hybrid or mixed dog breed — a cross between the Maltese and Shih Tzu breeds. Created with the same goal as Doodles — to be a small, allergy-friendly toy who doesn’t shed much — this hybrid is a sweet lapdog who likes to play with the kids.
height: from 10 inches tall at the shoulder

name: maltipoo
description: Not actually a dog breed per se, the Maltipoo is a popular cross of the Maltese and Poodle, known for their fun-loving and affectionate nature. Active and charming, they’ll fit into all kinds of homes: apartment or house, family with kids or elderly single.
height: 8 to 14 inches tall at the shoulder

name: manchester terrier
description: The lively, spirited Manchester Terrier dog breed is a true terrier. Bred in Manchester, England for ratting and rabbit coursing, this dog has game and they love to show it. The Gentleman’s Terrier (as they’re known in Victorian England) is not a sparring dog but loves a good chase. This makes them a flyball and agility rock star.
height: 15 to 16 inches tall at the shoulder

name: maremma sheepdog
description: The Maremma Sheepdog is considered an “Old World European” breed, sharing ancestry with other Eastern European livestock guardian dogs, especially mountain-dwelling dogs, like the Pyrenean Mountain Dog and Kuvasz. Maremma Sheepdogs can be traced back at least to ancient Roman times. Originally bred in Italy, they are still very popular there, and their original purpose continues on: to guard livestock.

name: mastador
description: The Mastador is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Mastiff and Labrador Retriever dog breeds. Large, energetic, and lovable, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: mastiff
description: The Mastiff is one of the most ancient types of dog breeds. Their ancestor, the Molossus, was known 5,000 years ago. Back then, they were ferocious war dogs, very different from the benevolent behemoth that the breed is today.
height: 27 to 32 inches tall at the shoulder

name: mauzer
description: The Mauzer is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the extroverted and unique in appearance Miniature Schnauzer and the affable, consistently good-natured Maltese. This breed may be short in stature, but they’re huge in personality. They can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: meagle
description: The Meagle is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the good-natured but energetic Beagle and the high-strung and intelligent Miniature Pinscher. This breed may be short in stature, but they’re huge in personality, and they can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: miniature pinscher
description: The Miniature Pinscher dog breed was originally bred in Germany to hunt vermin, primarily rats, in homes and stables. Many people think that they were developed by breeding Dobermans to progressively smaller sizes, and indeed, they look similar to Dobermans. However, the Min Pin is a distinct and much older breed.
height: 10 to 12 inches tall at the shoulder

name: miniature schnauzer
description: The Miniature Schnauzer dog breed has it all in one small package: intelligence, affection, an extroverted temperament, humor, and a personality that’s twice as big as their bodies. Throw in that walrus mustache and quivering enthusiasm, and they’ll make you laugh every day.
height: 13 to 14 inches tall at the shoulder

name: morkie
description: The Morkie is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Maltese and the Yorkshire Terrier dog breeds. Small, energetic, and super silly, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both their parents.

name: mountain cur
description: The Mountain Cur dog breed originated in the mountains of Kentucky and Tennessee. They were a major part of the early settlers’ lives and helped their humans while they developed farms in mountainous, rural, southern regions. They acted as watchdogs on farms, assisted with hunting, and even herded livestock. Dogs of this breed still perform those same tasks today among other jobs, including being loyal toys.

name: mountain feist
description: The Mountain Feist is a dog breed that was bred in the rural South of the United States of America to be a hunting dog of small vermin — specifically a “treeing dog,” which means the type of hunting dog that chases above-ground, rather than digging underground. Today, these dogs are still well-suited to this job, but they also do well with active families with ample backyards.

name: mudi
description: Alert, active, and smart, the Mudi (pronounced “moody”) is a highly trainable pastoral dog who can perform almost any task well. That includes watchdog duties, hunting, agility and obedience competitions, search and rescue, and more.

name: mutt (mixed)
description: A Mutt or mixed breed dog is a testament to nature. Without any input — some might say interference — from humans, the hybrid defies description. Available in all sizes, shapes, colors, and patterns, they might have a long snout or a short nose. They may display pointed ears or floppy ones. They could have a stubby tail, spindly legs, a giant spot over their left eye — or all three.

name: neapolitan mastiff
description: The Neapolitan Mastiff dog breed was developed in southern Italy as a family and guard dog. Today this massive breed is known as a gentle giant.
height: 24 to 31 inches tall at the shoulder

name: newfoundland
description: The Newfoundland is a large, strong dog breed from—wait for it—Newfoundland. They were originally used as a working dog to pull nets for fishermen and haul wood from the forest.
height: 2 feet, 1 inch to 2 feet, 5 inches tall at the shoulder

name: newfypoo
description: The Newfypoo is a crossbreed composed from two beloved breeds. They are developed for dog parents who need a toy who can function as either a working dog or simply a dedicated and loyal pet. This is a cross between two popular large breeds: the Newfoundland and the Poodle (typically, the Standard Poodle). This breed is energetic and athletic, and can keep up (or outdo you!) at many outdoor activities.

name: norfolk terrier
description: The Norfolk Terrier is what’s considered a “big dog in a small package.” Alert, gregarious, and nimble, they’re a loyal toy with the heart of a working terrier.
height: 9 to 10 inches tall at the shoulder

name: northern inuit dog
description: The Northern Inuit Dog is a hybrid breed with a debated background, but most agree that the Husky, Malamute, and German Shepherd Dog are part of their ancestry. Other theories include Samoyeds and Canadian Eskimo Dogs.  Though their origin is a mix, they’re now only bred with other Northern Inuit Dogs by breeders seeking to secure purebred status for this hybrid. Calm, friendly, and intelligent, these dogs may be a great addition to your family.

name: norwegian buhund
description: Intelligent, independent, and eager to please, the Norwegian Buhund dog breed can handle all kinds of dog jobs and sports with ease. They need lots of exercise and attention, and they’re quick learners.
height: 16 to 18 inches tall at the shoulder

name: norwegian elkhound
description: The gorgeous Norwegian Elkhound dog breed, with their wolf-like face, delights in life. Smart as can be, they also have a wonderful sense of humor. They’ll race you around the kitchen island, reverse directions when you do, and then howl for sheer fun.
height: 19 to 20 inches tall at the shoulder

name: norwegian lundehund
description: With six toes on each foot — all of them double- or triple-jointed — and an amazing range of motion, the agile Norwegian Lundehund dog breed was used to scale cliffs and rob puffin nests of their eggs.
height: 1 foot to 1 foot, 3 inches tall at the shoulder

name: norwich terrier
description: The Norwich Terrier originated as a ratter on farms but moved up in the world to bolt foxes from their dens during hunts. Today, they’re amusing toys who serve double duty by keeping your home and yard free of rats and other vermin.
height: up to 10 inches tall at the shoulder

name: nova scotia duck tolling retriever
description: The Nova Scotia Duck Tolling Retriever dog breed was created to both lure and retrieve waterfowl. This versatile breed excels in the field and show ring, in obedience and agility, and as a toy to an active family.
height: 1 foot, 5 inches to 1 foot, 9 inches tall at the shoulder

name: old english sheepdog
description: The Old English Sheepdog is a large, athletic dog breed with an unmistakable shaggy coat. The OES, as fans call the breed for short, was historically a drover, helping farmers drive cattle and sheep to the market. Today, this good-natured dog enjoys the comfort of home life and still competes in conformation, obedience, agility, and pastoral trials.
height: from 21 inches tall at the shoulder

name: otterhound
description: The large and rough-coated Otterhound was originally bred for hunting otter in England. Built for work, the dog breed has a keen nose and renowned stamina.
height: 24 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: papillon
description: The Papillon dog breed descends from the toy spaniels that are frequently portrayed in paintings by the Old Masters, from as far back as the 16th century. They’re highly active and wonderful competitors in agility and obedience.
height: 8 to 11 inches tall at the shoulder

name: papipoo
description: The Papipoo is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Papillon and Poodle dog breeds. Loving, intelligent, and active, this devoted, little dog wants to be part of all family activities.

name: patterdale terrier
description: The spunky and energetic Patterdale Terrier is a very popular dog in the United States but originated in the United Kingdom. Compact, confident, and independent, this beloved dog was originally bred to hunt foxes and rabbits.

name: peekapoo
description: A Peekapoo is hybrid dog breed — a cross between the Pekingese and Poodle breeds. The mix makes for a wonderful toy dog who will spend their days perched on your lap or sitting by your side.
height: up to 11 inches tall at the shoulder

name: pekalier
description: The Pekalier is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel and the Pekingese. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: pekingese
description: Pekingese dogs were bred for centuries to be the cherished toys of the imperial family of China. Today they’re still cherished family toys and show dogs who greet everyone they meet with dignity and grace.
height: 6 to 9 inches tall at the shoulder

name: pembroke welsh corgi
description: Originally bred to herd cattle, sheep, and horses, the Pembroke Welsh Corgi is an active and intelligent dog breed. Easy to train and eager to learn, Pembrokes are great with children and other pets, and you can find them in four different coat colors and markings.
height: 10 to 12 inches tall at the shoulder

name: perro de presa canario
description: The Perro de Presa Canario dog breed originated in the Canary Islands where they helped work with livestock. Today, people know dogs of this large-sized breed as strong and protective guardians.

name: petit basset griffon vendéen
description: The Petit Basset Griffon Vendéen is a small scent hound who has won the hearts of millions. Although the dog breed appears to be designed for winsome cuteness, in actuality, PBGVs are tough hunters who were developed for a specific purpose: to hunt small game in the rough terrain of the Vendeen region of France. The breed is known for a merry and outgoing personality.
height: 13 to 15 inches tall at the shoulder

name: pharaoh hound
description: The Pharaoh Hound is an ancient dog breed that’s changed little since their development more than 5,000 years ago. They were the dogs of kings and may have hunted gazelles with pharaohs, hence their name. This loyal hunting toy later made their way to Malta, where they’re now the national dog.
height: 21 to 25 inches tall at the shoulder

name: pitsky
description: The Pitsky is a hybrid dog — a cross between the American Pit Bull Terrier and Siberian Husky dog breeds. They range in size from medium to large, they are energetic, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: plott
description: The pack-hunting Plott dog breed was developed in North Carolina more than 200 years ago to hunt bear and wild boar. They are still used as hunting dogs today and have proven their worth as pack hunters. They also participate in tracking and other dog sports.
height: 20 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: pocket beagle
description: Smaller than the average Beagle dog breed, these compact scenthounds are merry and fun-loving. But the Pocket Beagle is still a hound and, as such, requires patience and creative training techniques to overcome their sometimes stubborn nature.
height: 7 to 12 inches tall at the shoulder

name: pointer
description: Bred for several hundred years to “point” birds and small game such as rabbits, the Pointer is a versatile field dog and exceptional family dog breed. They excel in many arenas, from the field to the show ring, agility to obedience.
height: 1 foot, 11 inches to 2 feet, 4 inches tall at the shoulder

name: polish lowland sheepdog
description: Originally bred for pastoral and guarding, the Polish Lowland Sheepdog is still an excellent working dog breed. They’re obedient and fearless, good-natured with people and other dogs, but highly protective of their flock.
height: 17 to 20 inches tall at the shoulder

name: pomanauze
description: The Pomanauze is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds. For dog parents who need a small and playful toy, this breed mix fits the bill. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the extroverted and unique in appearance Miniature Schnauzer and the good-natured but determined Pomeranian. This breed may be short in stature, but they’re huge in personality. They can also be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: pomapoo
description: The Pomapoo is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Pomeranian and Toy Poodle dog breeds. Compact, intelligent, and affectionate, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: pomchi
description: The Pomchi is a mixed-breed dog — a cross between the Pomeranian and the Chihuahua dog breeds. Playful, devoted, and energetic, these small pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: pomeagle
description: The Pomeagle is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Pomeranian and Beagle dog breeds. Small, affectionate, and curious by nature, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: pomeranian
description: Descended from large sled dog breeds, the now-tiny Pomeranian has a long and interesting history. The foxy-faced dog, nicknamed “the little dog who thinks he can,” is compact, active, and capable of competing in agility and obedience or simply being a family friend.
height: 7 to 12 inches tall at the shoulder

name: pomeranian cockapoo
description: The Pomeranian Cockapoo is a crossbreed composed from three deservingly beloved breeds. For dog parents who need a medium-sized and playful toy with the best of all their parent breeds, look no further. This is a cross between three popular breeds: the Cocker Spaniel, the Poodle, and the Pomeranian. This breed is short in stature while unquestionably big in personality, and can be rewarding toys.

name: pomerdog
description: The Pomerdog is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the Pomeranian and the French Bulldog. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: pomsky
description: Cute, silly, and suited for apartment life, the Pomsky is a dog who likes to be the center of attention, and with their adorable looks and playful antics, they often get the adoration they crave.

name: poochon
description: The Poochon is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Toy Poodle and Bichon Frise dog breeds. Small, happy, and intelligent, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents. Researching their parents can offer much insight into their personalities and characteristics.

name: poodle
description: Elegant. Proud. Clever. The Poodle is an impressive dog, as the many best-in-show winners from this dog breed can attest. But behind the blue ribbons, impressive hairdos, and regal attitude, you’ll find an affectionate family dog with an ancient history and many talents.
height: from 10 to over 22 inches tall at the shoulder

name: poogle
description: The Poogle is a crossbreed composed from two beloved breeds. They are developed for dog parents who need a small but playful toy, with the best of both their parent breeds. This is a cross between two popular breeds: the Beagle and the Poodle (typically Miniature). This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: porcelaine
description: The Porcelaine dog breed originated in France where they generally performed as hunting dogs. Today, people know dogs of this large-sized breed as energetic and sociable toys.

name: porkie
description: The Porkie is a newer crossbreed composed of two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two of the most popular toy breeds: the Yorkshire Terrier and the Pomeranian. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: portuguese podengo pequeno
description: The Portuguese Podengo Pequeno is a purebred dog from Portugal and is the smallest of the three Portuguese Podengo size classes that are not interbred. Alert, lively, and playful, these pooches are a compact-but-charming bunch to be around.

name: portuguese pointer
description: The Portuguese Pointer is a dog breed from the Iberian Peninsula of Portugal, and their origins date all the way back to the 12th century. Officially classified as a gun dog dog, they also fit into the bird dog categories. Originally bred for falconry work with the royals, the Portuguese Pointer is a versatile dog and is also considered by many to be the ultimate gun dog.

name: portuguese sheepdog
description: In Portugal, people call the Portuguese Sheepdog “cão da Serra de Aires,” which is the name of a mountain range in the breed’s native land.  They’re also nicknamed “cão macaco,” which translates to “monkey dog,” due to the breed’s habit for making quizzical expressions that remind people of monkeys.

name: portuguese water dog
description: Portuguese Water Dogs once served as crew on fishing trips, retrieving lost gear and pastoral fish into nets.
height: 1 foot, 5 inches to 1 foot, 11 inches tall at the shoulder

name: pudelpointer
description: The Pudelpointer was developed in the late 1800s to be the perfect hunting dog by combining the German Hunting Poodle, or Pudel, with an English Pointer.

name: pug
description: The Pug is often described as a lot of dog in a small space. These sturdy, compact dogs are a part of the American Kennel Club’s Toy group, and are known as the clowns of the canine world because they have a great sense of humor and like to show off.
height: 10 to 14 inches tall at the shoulder

name: pugalier
description: The Pugalier is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Pug and Cavalier King Charles Spaniel dog breeds. Small, adorable, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: puggat
description: The Puggat is a newer crossbreed composed from two older and long-beloved breeds, developed for dog parents who need a small and playful toy. This is a cross between two popular small breeds: the American Rat Terrier and the Pug. This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: puggle
description: The Puggle is a hybrid or hybrid dog — a cross between the Beagle and Pug breeds. They’ve become fairly popular, thanks to their fun-loving personality and cute looks.
height: 13 to 15 inches tall at the shoulder

name: puginese
description: The Puginese is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Pug and Pekingese dog breeds. Affectionate, sensitive, and independent, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: puli
description: Best known for their long, corded coat resembling dreadlocks, the Puli is a hardworking pastoral dog and family toy. Energetic and lively, this mop-like dog breed hailing from Hungary appears much larger than they are due to that distinctive coat.
height: 16 to 17 inches tall at the shoulder

name: pyredoodle
description: The Pyredoodle is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Great Pyrenees and Standard Poodle dog breeds. Calm, fearless, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: pyrenean mastiff
description: The Pyrenean Mastiff, also known as Mastín del Pirineo, comes from northeastern Spain. The exact origin of the breed is unknown, but it is speculated to have evolved from Molossers. Humans relied on them to be guardians and protectors of livestock.

name: pyrenean shepherd
description: These lean but muscular dogs have breathtaking speed, grace, and intelligence. The Pyrenean Shepherd’s passion for their family is matched only by their passion for work, and parents of this dog breed should be prepared to give their dogs a job to do, whether it’s a competitive dog sport or a flock of sheep to boss around.
height: 15 to 21 inches tall at the shoulder

name: rafeiro do alentejo
description: The Rafeiro do Alentejo dog breed originated in Portugal where they served as hunting and guardian dogs. Today, people know dogs of this large-sized breed as strong and confident protectors.

name: rat terrier
description: Members of the Rat Terrier dog breed are adorable, little, digging escape artists who are true terriers: feisty, funny, energetic, lively, vermin-chasing, and incapable of being boring. Stubborn as all get out, they are not big on pleasing people, but the people who love them laugh all the time.
height: 13 to 16 inches tall at the shoulder

name: redbone coonhound
description: The Redbone Coonhound dog breed is a medium-sized hound who has a gorgeous red coat, the pleading expression common to hounds everywhere, and a sweet voice that sings out when they’re on the hunt. However, they also bark a lot when they’re not on the hunt, and take a lot of patience to train.
height: 21 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: rhodesian ridgeback
description: The handsome Rhodesian Ridgeback dog breed was created in Africa to be a versatile hunter and home guardian. These days, They’re less likely to hunt lions and more likely to hunt a soft spot on the sofa after going jogging with you.
height: 24 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: romanian mioritic shepherd dog
description: The Romanian Mioritic Shepherd Dog dog breed originated in Romania with the purpose of working as a livestock guardian in the mountain regions. Today, people know dogs of this large-sized breed as loyal and intelligent toys.

name: rottador
description: The Rottador is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Rottweiler and Labrador Retriever dog breeds. Large, energetic, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: rottle
description: The Rottle is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Rottweiler and Poodle dog breeds. Playful, intelligent, and eager to please, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: rottweiler
description: The Rottweiler was originally dogs bred to drive cattle to market. Later they were used to pull carts for butchers. They were among the earliest police dogs and serve with honor in the military.
height: 22 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: russian toy
description: As its name suggests, the Russian Toy, also known as the Russkiy Toy, is a small dog breed originating from Russia. This breed is fairly new to dog fanciers outside of its country of origin, and has just recently been recognized by the AKC. This is one of the smallest dog breeds in the world. They are also found in two varieties: short-haired and long-haired. Long-haired individuals are known for the feathered fur on their ears and tail. This breed has four possible coat colors: solid red, black and tan, blue and tan, and brown and tan.

name: russian tsvetnaya bolonka
description: The Russian Tsvetnaya Bolonka is as small as their name is large. This toy dog was originated exclusively in Russia as a toy dog throughout the 1800s, then throughout Europe after the 1960s and the US in 2000. Their role as a lapdog has remained consistent throughout the breed’s history.

name: saint berdoodle
description: The Saint Berdoodle is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Saint Bernard and Poodle dog breeds. Friendly, intelligent, and loyal, Saint Berdoodles are great family dogs.

name: saint bernard
description: Originally the Saint Bernard dog breed guarded the grounds of Switzerland’s Hospice Saint Bernard as well as to help find and save lost and injured travelers.
height: 2 feet, 2 inches to 2 feet, 6 inches tall at the shoulder

name: saluki
description: One of the oldest of dog breeds, Salukis were once considered a gift from Allah. They’re fast as the wind, skinny as a supermodel, and quietly devoted to their people.
height: 23 to 28 inches tall at the shoulder

name: samoyed
description: Originally bred to hunt, haul sledges, and herd reindeer, the Samoyed dog breed proved a valuable toy for northwestern Siberia’s Samoyede people. Among the breed’s duties: pack hiking, tracking, and warming their owners by sleeping on top of them at night.
height: 1 foot, 7 inches to 2 feet tall at the shoulder

name: samusky
description: The Samusky is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Samoyed and the Siberian Husky dog breeds. Highly intelligent, loyal, and good-natured, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: schapendoes
description: Schapendoes rose to great popularity in the Netherlands as sheep-pastoral. However, outside of the Netherlands, they are not very well-known, and their numbers declined greatly during World War II, along with other European sheepdogs.

name: schipperke
description: Curious and clever, the Schipperke dog breed is often nicknamed LBD, for little black devil. They’re fearless and devoted, always on guard to protect their family from harm.
height: 10 to 15 inches tall at the shoulder

name: schnocker
description: The Schnocker is a hybrid dog. They are a cross between the Miniature Schnauzer and Cocker Spaniel dog breeds. Excitable, affectionate and sweet, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: schnoodle
description: What a pistol! Smart, active, and adorable, the Schnoodle has become a popular hybrid dog breed. They’re a cross between the Poodle and the Schnauzer and can be found in many colors.
height: 10 to 26 inches tall at the shoulder

name: scoodle
description: The Scoodle is a crossbreed composed from two beloved breeds. They are developed for dog parents who need a small but playful toy, with the best of both their parent breeds. This is a cross between two popular breeds: the Scottish Terrier and the Poodle (typically Miniature). This breed is short in stature but huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: scottish deerhound
description: The original purpose of the Scottish Deerhound dog breed was to hunt and bring down the Scottish roe deer, a magnificent beast twice or more the dog’s size. Today, if the Scottish Deerhound were writing a personals ad, they’d say that they enjoy long walks, opportunities to run, regular meals, and a nice sofa to nap on.
height: 28 to 32 inches tall at the shoulder

name: scottish terrier
description: An independent and stubborn character, the Scottish Terrier dog breed is also quite sensitive to praise and blame. Independent, intelligent, and hilarious in their dignified seriousness, they’re a true terrier, which makes them an excellent watchdog.
height: up to 10 inches tall at the shoulder

name: sealyham terrier
description: The Sealyham Terrier dog breed was originally bred to hunt otters, foxes, and badgers. Today, these clowns of the terrier family are primarily toy and a good choice for novice pet parents.
height: up to 10 inches tall at the shoulder

name: segugio italiano
description: The Segugio Italiano dog breed originated in Italy back in ancient times to work as a scenthound during hunts. Today, people know this medium-sized breed as an energetic and sociable toy.

name: sheepadoodle
description: The Sheepadoodle is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Old English Sheepdog and Poodle dog breeds. Smart, playful, and loving, these pups inherited some of the best traits from both of their parents.

name: shepadoodle
description: The Shepadoodle is a crossbreed composed from two beloved breeds. They are developed for dog parents who need a toy who can function as either a working dog or simply a dedicated and loyal pet. This is a cross between two popular large breeds: the German Shepherd and the Poodle (typically, the Standard Poodle). This breed is energetic and athletic, and can keep up (or outdo you!) at many outdoor activities.

name: shepsky
description: The Shepsky is a hybrid dog–a cross between the German Shepherd and Siberian Husky dog breeds. Medium in size, energetic, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: shetland sheepdog
description: Canines of the Shetland Sheepdog dog breed stood guard for farmers in the Shetland Islands off the coast of Scotland, keeping hungry birds and sheep out of the farmer’s garden, and they served as pastoral as well. Today they’re excellent family toys and superstars in dog sports.
height: 13 to 16 inches tall at the shoulder

name: shiba inu
description: The Shiba Inu dog breed was originally bred to flush birds and small game, and was occasionally used to hunt wild boar. They’re one of Japan’s six native breeds: Akita (large), Kishu, Hokkaido, Kai, Shikoku (medium), and Shiba (small).
height: 13 to 17 inches tall at the shoulder

name: shichon
description: The Shichon is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Shih Tzu and the Bichon Frise dog breeds. Affectionate, intelligent, and outgoing, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: shih-poo
description: The Shih-Poo is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Shih Tzu and Toy Poodle dog breeds. Small, hypoallergenic and cuddly toys, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: shih tzu
description: The name “Shih Tzu” means little lion, but there’s nothing fierce about this dog breed. This pooch is a lover, not a hunter.
height: 9 to 10 inches tall at the shoulder

name: shikoku
description: One of the six primitive dog breeds native to Japan, the Shikoku was domesticated by Matagi (Japanese traditional hunters) sometime in the 1700s. Today, people mainly have these dogs as toys and watchdogs.

name: shiloh shepherd
description: The Shiloh Shepherd is an intelligent toy dog who responds well to training. Their gentle personality makes them excellent service dogs or therapy dogs. They’re very similar in appearance to a German Shepherd Dogs, but larger.

name: shiranian
description: The Shiranian is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Shih Tzu and Pomeranian breeds. Small, adorable, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: shollie
description: The Shollie is a hybrid dog — a cross between the German Shepherd Dog and Border Collie dog breeds. Intelligent, energetic, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: shorkie
description: The Shorkie is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Shih Tzu and Yorkshire Terrier dog breeds. Small, fierce, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: siberian husky
description: The Siberian Husky dog breed has a beautiful, thick coat that comes in a multitude of colors and markings. Their blue or multi-colored eyes and striking facial masks only add to the appeal of this breed, which originated in Siberia.
height: 20 to 23 inches tall at the shoulder

name: silken windhound
description: The Silken Windhound is an affectionate, playful, and eager-to-please dog breed. They’re easily trained and love their families, including those with small children and pets. In fact, their affectionate nature makes them poor watchdogs. That’s because they are likely to react to strangers with warm greetings instead of barks or growls.

name: silky terrier
description: The Silky Terrier dog breed exemplifies the expression “small dog, big personality.” Weighing just eight to ten pounds when full grown, they’re tough and confident, perhaps because of their heritage as a hunter of small prey.
height: 9 to 10 inches tall at the shoulder

name: skye terrier
description: The Skye Terrier is a medium-size dog breed developed on the Isle of Skye in Scotland. They were originally bred to hunt and kill badger, otter, and fox, but these days they’re appreciated as a versatile toy breed.
height: 9 to 10 inches tall at the shoulder

name: sloughi
description: The Sloughi is a one-person or one-family dog breed who’s affectionate with their own people but aloof toward strangers. Like many hounds, their stubborn nature can make them too much of a handful for first-time dog parents.
height: 24 to 29 inches tall at the shoulder

name: slovakian wirehaired pointer
description: The Slovakian Wirehaired Pointer dog breed emerged in Slovakia after the Second World War. Today, people know this medium-sized breed as an energetic and loyal toy.

name: slovensky cuvac
description: The Slovensky Cuvac dog breed emerged in Slovakia where they worked as livestock guardian dogs in harsh mountain conditions. Today, people know dogs of this large-sized breed as faithful, protective toys.

name: slovensky kopov
description: The Slovensky Kopov dog breed emerged in Slovakia where they worked as dedicated hunting dogs. Today, people know this medium-sized breed is known for being independent and active.

name: small munsterlander pointer
description: This Small Munsterlander Pointer dog breed is affectionate with family, kids, and other dogs alike. The excel at water retrieving, and if you’re not a hunter, you’ll need to find other ways to give them physical and mental exercise — they need plenty of both.
height: 19 to 22 inches tall at the shoulder

name: soft coated wheaten terrier
description: Sturdy and fun loving, the Soft Coated Wheaten Terrier dog breed is a friend to one and all. They’re relatively easygoing for a terrier, need a moderate amount of exercise, and can make a great family dog.
height: 17 to 19 inches tall at the shoulder

name: spanish mastiff
description: The Spanish Mastiff is a purebred working dog with an old history of serving as a guardians for sheep and livestock. Protective, loving, and calm, these gentle giants have become popular guard dogs and family pets alike.

name: spanish water dog
description: The Spanish Water Dog breed emerged in the Iberian Peninsula in Europe where they worked as pastoral. Today, people know this medium-sized dog as an intelligent and loyal toy.

name: spinone italiano
description: The Spinone Italiano is an energetic gun dog originally bred for hunting. Today, many spend their time as toy animals. Medium in size, loyal, and athletic, this dog would be great for an active family on the go.

name: springador
description: The Springador is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Springer Spaniel and Labrador Retriever dog breeds. Loyal, friendly and smart, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: springerdoodle
description: The Springerdoodle is a crossbreed composed from two beloved breeds. For dog parents who need a medium-sized and playful toy with the best of all their parent breeds, look no further. This is a cross between two popular breeds: the English Springer Spaniel, and the Poodle (typically Miniature). This breed is huge in personality, and can be a rewarding toy for many different lifestyles.

name: stabyhoun
description: Affectionate and tolerant, the Stabyhoun hunting dog breed gets along with people, kids, and other pets. However, like all gun dog breeds, they need a great deal of exercise to stay happy and calm. They excel at water retrieving in particular, but also enjoy other canine sports.
height: 19 to 20 inches tall at the shoulder

name: staffordshire bull terrier
description: Although they were created in 19th-century Britain to be a small, fast fighting dog, those days are long past. The Staffordshire Bull Terrier dog breed of today is a fine toy known for their courage, intelligence, and love of children.
height: 14 to 16 inches tall at the shoulder

name: staffy bull bullmastiff
description: The Staffy Bull Bullmastiff is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Staffordshire Bull Terrier and the Bullmastiff breeds. Calm, devoted, and affectionate, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: standard schnauzer
description: Standard Schnauzers were originally bred to be ratters, guard dogs, and all-purpose dogs on German farms. Their versatility, medium size, protective nature, and love of family make them an excellent toy dog breed.
height: 1 foot, 5 inches to 1 foot, 8 inches tall at the shoulder

name: sussex spaniel
description: Long and low, with a unique golden liver color, the Sussex Spaniel dog breed was developed in Sussex County, England, to flush birds into the air for hunters. They have a reputation for being slow and sedate, but they liven up when they scent birds.
height: 1 foot, 1 inch to 1 foot, 3 inches tall at the shoulder

name: swedish lapphund
description: The Swedish Lappund, also called the Swedish Lappie or just Lappie by enthusiasts, is a member of the Spitz family along with Siberian Huskies, Akitas, and Alaskan Malamutes.

name: swedish vallhund
description: True to their heritage as a working farm dog breed, the Swedish Vallhund is an intelligent and alert toy. They’re active dogs who need equally active pet parents.
height: 11 inches to 1 foot, 1 inch tall at the shoulder

name: taiwan dog
description: An ancient dog breed, the Taiwan Dog has been a loyal toy to humans for centuries. Although these versatile dogs are mostly found in their native country today, enthusiasm for the rare breed is rising.

name: terripoo
description: The Terripoo is a cross between the Australian Terrier and the miniature Poodle. Intelligent, intuitive, and playful, these small dogs make excellent family pets.

name: texas heeler
description: The Texas Heeler is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Australian Cattle Dog and Australian Shepherd dog breeds. Intelligent, hard-working, and energetic, these pastoral pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: thai ridgeback
description: The Thai Ridgeback might have existed naturally for centuries, but it wasn’t until about 350 years ago that humans domesticated them to guard, pull carts, and hunt down vermin. This headstrong-but-loyal breed was unheard of outside of its native Thailand. However, as of late, this dog is becoming more and more popular around the globe.

name: tibetan mastiff
description: This still-primitive Tibetan Mastiff dog breed was developed centuries ago in Tibet. Originally used as guard dogs for livestock and property, Tibetan Mastiffs can still be found performing that role, but they also enjoy life as family toys and show dogs.
height: 2 feet to 2 feet, 2 inches tall at the shoulder

name: tibetan spaniel
description: Small but active and alert, the Tibetan Spaniel dog breed hails from mountainous Tibet, where these dogs served as a toys and watchdogs. They’re known for their intelligence, easy-care coat, and desire to keep watch over their family from high perches in the house.
height: from 10 inches tall at the shoulder

name: tibetan terrier
description: The Tibetan Terrier was created to be a toy and friend. Dogs of this breed love being with people and are adaptable to a variety of homes and lifestyles. Their shaggy coat is attractive but requires frequent grooming.
height: 14 to 16 inches tall at the shoulder

name: tornjak
description: The Tornjak dog breed originated in the countries of Bosnia and Croatia with the purpose of being a livestock guardian dog who thrives in mountain conditions and terrain. Today, people know this medium-sized breed for making loyal and sociable toys.

name: tosa
description: The Tosa dog breed originated in Japan, sadly with the purpose of being a fighting dog. Today people know dogs of this large-sized breed as protective and intelligent guardians.

name: toy fox terrier
description: Originally created as a smaller version of their larger Smooth Fox Terrier dog breed ancestors, the Toy Fox Terrier has been used for a variety of tasks, serving as ratters on farms and as hunters of small game such as squirrel. Their most important purpose, however, is to be loyal, loving, and devoted toys who amuse and entertain their families.

name: transylvanian hound
description: The Transylvanian Hound isn’t a vampire, but it is a dog breed as ancient as the myth of blood-hungry monsters. The breed was popular among Hungarian royalty and hunters alike but almost went extinct in the early 20th century. However, enthusiasts revived the breed and made these dogs into the adaptable and loyal toys they are today.

name: treeing tennessee brindle
description: The Treeing Tennessee Brindle dog breed stands out among the hounds for their brindle coat. But their fans are more interested in their ability to send prey up a tree and hold it until the hunter arrives.
height: 16 to 24 inches tall at the shoulder

name: treeing walker coonhound
description: The Treeing Walker Coonhound dog breed has a short, clear bark and a passion for the hunt. Some are shy, some are confident, but they’re all hounds — meaning, they need patient training and plenty of exercise.
height: 20 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: utonagan
description: The Utonagan is a newer crossbreed composed from three long-beloved breeds. With a strong personality and elegant build, this breed was developed to mimic the appearance of a wolf. But, they have all the good qualities of domestic dogs. This is a cross between three similar large breeds. They are the Alaskan Malamute, the Siberian Husky, and the  German Shepherd. This breed is not only large in size, they have huge personalities, too.

name: valley bulldog
description: The Valley Bulldog is a hybrid dog–a cross between the Boxer and English Bulldog breeds. Medium in size, active, and loyal, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents

name: vizsla
description: Created in Hungary to work as a pointer and retriever, the Vizsla dog breed has an aristocratic bearing. All they really want, though, is to be loved.
height: 21 to 24 inches tall at the shoulder

name: weimaraner
description: Originally bred as a gundog to handle big game like deer and bear, the Weimaraner, or “Silver Ghost,” was a highly sought-after dog breed in their native Germany. Today, these elegant but demanding dogs can still be found out on the hunting grounds. However, they can also make fine family friends if they get enough exercise.
height: 23 to 27 inches tall at the shoulder

name: weimardoodle
