description: The Weimardoodle is a crossbreed composed from two beloved breeds. They are developed for dog parents who need a toy who can function as either a working dog or simply a dedicated and loyal pet. This is a cross between two popular large breeds: the Weimaraner and the Poodle (typically, the Standard Poodle). This breed is energetic and athletic, and can keep up (or outdo you!) at many outdoor activities.

name: welsh springer spaniel
description: The Welsh Springer Spaniel dog breed was developed as a gundog to flush, or spring, game in the field. A faithful toy, they’re a favorite of discriminating hunters and families.
height: 17 to 19 inches tall at the shoulder

name: welsh terrier
description: The Welsh Terrier dog breed‘s zest for life is contagious, and they always enjoy themselves to the fullest. Bred to hunt independently, with all the self-determination and intelligence that entails, the happy and lively Welshie rarely gets tired and wants to spend their days having fun, fun, fun!
height: 14 to 15 inches tall at the shoulder

name: west highland white terrier
description: The best way to describe the wee West Highland White Terrier dog breed from Scotland is simply to say that they’re so full of self-esteem that they know they’re the best thing around. Always on the lookout for a good time, they’ll make you laugh while they entertain themselves.
height: 10 to 11 inches tall at the shoulder

name: westiepoo
description: The Westiepoo is a hybrid dog — a cross between the West Highland White Terrier and Poodle dog breeds. Clever, active, and affectionate, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: whippet
description: The Whippet dog breed was a hunter’s best friend, speedily going after rabbits and other small game. Today the breed competes in agility, flyball, lure coursing, rally, and obedience and is a loving therapy dog.
height: 18 to 22 inches tall at the shoulder

name: whoodle
description: The Whoodle is a hybrid dog — a cross between the Soft-Coated Wheaten Terrier and Poodle dog breeds. Playful, friendly, and active, these pups inherited some of the best qualities from both of their parents.

name: wirehaired pointing griffon
description: The Wirehaired Pointing Griffon is a happy and loving dog breed. They make excellent gundogs or family toys, and they suffers from comparatively few diseases. With their sense of humor and lively nature, they’re a good match for an energetic family looking for a dog to be part of their daily activities.
height: 20 to 24 inches tall at the shoulder

name: working kelpie
description: The Working Kelpie dog breed originated in Australia with the purpose of being a working dog who specializes in dealing with sheep and livestock. Today, people know this medium-sized breed for making attentive and energetic toys.

name: xiasi
description: The Xiasi is a breed that few of us will have the pleasure of seeing in person. However, there’s lots to admire about this rare white dog. The Xiasi, also known as the Xiasi Hound, hails from China — and less than 300 remain.

name: xoloitzcuintli
description: The Xoloitzcuintli dog breed — sometimes called the Mexican Hairless or just Xolo — may well have descended from the first dogs to set paw on the North American continent.
height: 1 foot, 6 inches to 1 foot, 11 inches tall at the shoulder

name: yakutian laika
description: The Yakutian Laika is an ancient dog breed from the cold region of Yakutia, an area of northern Russia with extreme temperatures. The Sahka people of the region developed the breed not only to be an impressive sled dog, but a part of the human family as well.

name: yorkipoo
description: A fun-loving “designer dog” — and therefore a mixed dog breed — a Yorkipoo is a cross between the Yorkshire Terrier and a Toy or Miniature Poodle. Intelligent, affectionate, and gentle, they make a delightful toy. They also fit in perfectly to apartment life, especially if you don’t mind the barking.
height: 7 to 15 inches tall at the shoulder

name: yorkshire terrier
description: Small in size but big in personality, the Yorkshire Terrier makes a feisty but loving toy. The most popular toy dog breed in the United States, the “Yorkie” has won many fans with their devotion to their owners, their elegant looks, and their suitability to apartment living.
height: 8 to 9 inches tall at the shoulder
